title: copper carrots(carrot salad)
directions: Cut carrots crosswise in 1/4-inch rings and cook in boiling water until barely done.
Drain and place in large bowl.
Separate onion slices into rings; add with green pepper to carrot mixture. Combine tomato soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper in blender.
Pour over carrots.
Marinate overnight.
Makes 8 cups.

title: broccoli-parmesan bake
directions: Thaw broccoli and stir with the onion, water and mayonnaise until mixed.
Spoon into a shallow, nonstick baking dish.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: smooth n creamy frosting
directions: Combine filling, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Beat slowly (lowest speed) until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cake at once.
Makes 4 cups frosting or enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: salmon caesar
directions: Beat eggs, milk and soup.
Stir in croutons, salmon, onions and green peppers.
Pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set in center.

title: german punch (ananas bowle)(pineapple-bowl)
directions: Place pineapple in punch bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add rum; let stand for 2 hours.
Add wine and champagne or soda water. Strawberries can also be used.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Chill at least one hour (can be served immediately).
Store no longer than 3 days.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: hash brown casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Make sure hash browns are thawed. Mix together well the hash browns with all ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
In butter, cook onion 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in flour, salt and mustard, then milk.
Cook, stirring until thick and smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt.
In casserole, arrange layer of carrots and cheese; repeat, ending with carrots. Pour sauce over carrots.
Top with bread cubes.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: glazed carrots with grapes
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and set aside.
Stir water into cornstarch and set aside.
Combine orange juice, sugar and wine; bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in carrots and grapes.
Serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: **pineapple coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, apples, pineapple, marshmallows, celery and enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Toss slightly.

title: banana pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers longways.
Cut out the seed.
Slice enough to fill 3 quarts; pack in the jars.
Boil rest of ingredients to dissolve sugar and salt; pour over pickles and seal. Cold pack 10 minutes.

title: self-filling cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin pans, 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar until light.
Add salt and egg.
Beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto each cupcake.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: great grandma regiec's fruit and nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients all at once and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in a greased tube pan.

title: easy karo pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir in first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Then cool.

title: vanilla pudding or pie mix
directions: Mix together egg yolks, cornstarch and 1 cup of milk.
Put 1 1/2 cups of milk and sugar in a kettle and before it comes to a boil, add egg yolks, cornstarch and milk mixture.
Stir until thick, then add margarine and vanilla.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in greased tins.
Remove from pans and dip in melted oleo and roll in sugar.

title: chili con queso soup from neiman-marcus(tortilla)
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened. Add chilies and tomatoes. Cook mixture 8 to 10 minutes over moderate heat until liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cream cheese. Maintain moderate to low heat until cheese melts. Stir in broth, half and half, lemon juice and seasonings. Heat soup over moderate heat until hot, but do not boil.

title: walnut short bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix all ingredients and pat into a pan.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread fantasia stained glass cookies(great christmas dessert)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices. Set aside.
In a separate bowl, cream butter and sugar at medium speed until fluffy.
Add molasses and water, beating until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture and beat at low speed just until mixed.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all together well and pour into a large casserole dish or square pan. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Bake at 425° for a glass container.

title: four day make ahead sour cream torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) round pans. In large bowl, blend all cake ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed; pour into pans.
Cool cake in pan on cooling rack 15 minutes; remove.
Cool completely. Split each layer in half forming four layers.
Fill and frost layers with sour cream coconut filling.
If desired, garnish with pecans and maraschino cherries.
Store covered in refrigerator 12 to 14 servings.

title: oriental zucchini and onion
directions: Cut onion and zucchini into small strips (julienne).
Heat olive oil in large, nonstick skillet.
Saute until veggies are tender.
Drizzle with soy sauce to taste (about 1 to 2 tablespoons is usually enough).
Stir to coat with soy sauce and serve immediately.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and drain.
Cut off florets.
Chop some of the tender stems near florets.
Remove the tougher stems and peel the main stock.
Slice in circles.
Mix all ingredients.
Let chill for about 2 hours or overnight.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 375°.

title: golden wassail
directions: Pour juices into percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket.
Perk and serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place chicken into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a saucepan, combine tomatoes, cornstarch and oregano.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Pour heated sauce over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Yields 4 servings.

title: jane's shrimp scampi and baked stuff shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
In a baking dish, melt butter and add all ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Let cool.
Place shrimp in a baking dish.
Pour almost all mixture on shrimp.
Mix rest with bread crumbs.
Spread over top, rest of mixture or dry bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes; then lower oven to 350° and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Voila!

title: date nut pinwheels
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll out and spread with date mixture.
Wrap and chill several hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and clean shrimp. Chop up shells and saute in butter over low heat, 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not bring to boil.
Drain off butter.
Squeeze shells in cheese cloth to remove remaining butter.

title: egg nog punch
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar gradually.
Add rum, brandy and vanilla extract.
Add milk.
Fold whipped cream in last. Sprinkle with nutmeg for dressing.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add rest of ingredients and spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. (Double recipe in 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Bake 25 minutes or until crusty at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: pennsylvania dutch noodles and apples
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Place half of noodles, then all of apples in the dish.
Sprinkle with half of the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place remaining noodles on top and sprinkle with rest of sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickled beets
directions: Slice beets.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook over medium heat. Bring to slow boil and let cook a few minutes.
Take off and let cool.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice pickles thin.
Combine
with salt.
Let stand for 3 hours and
drain.
Combine all the other ingredients, bringing to a boil.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: barb's dried beef cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix with all other ingredients and refrigerate.
Let it season overnight. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: crab cioppino
directions: Simmer sauce approximately 4 hours to a medium-thick consistency.
Put olive oil in large pot.
Limp celery and garlic. Add tomato sauce, water and wine.
Simmer (no cover).
Place fish in large pot with lid.
Forty-five minutes before you want to serve, pour sauce over fish, cover and steam 30 to 40 minutes. Halibut will break up when done.
Serves 8.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash and remove leaves from beets. Place in a large kettle of water. Bring to a boil and cook until skins will slip off when held in cold water and gently twist with fingers. Rinse lightly and drain in a colander.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; cool and cut in pieces.
Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Arrange peas and carrots over chicken.
Mix broth, celery soup and chicken soup and pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Mix flour, buttermilk and melted margarine and pour over chicken pie.
Salt and pepper may be added to the crust.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Then place raw chicken in rice mixture.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: stupendous lemon pepper chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in lemon juice, margarine, 3 teaspoons lemon pepper and 2 teaspoons seasoned salt for 10 minutes or longer. Combine flour, 2 teaspoons lemon pepper and 1 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Coat chicken in this, heat 1/2 cup margarine, brown chicken lightly in this.
Place on cookie sheet and cook.

title: mexican rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in oil. Add garlic, cumin and rice. Cook 3 minutes on medium heat. Add meat and remaining ingredients except cheese. Bring to a boil. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until rice is soft. Sprinkle with cheese and heat uncovered in oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients and sift together in a large bowl. Add oil, apples and vanilla.
Beat by hand until well blended. Beat eggs and add sugar gradually.
Fold egg mixture into apple mixture and blend.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve plain or top with Cool Whip or whipping cream.
Also serve as a morning coffee cake.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until clear and thick. Cool, then add 1 quart berries. Pour into a baked pie shell and put in refrigerator until set, about 2 to 3 hours. Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: delia's macaroni salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and add the remaining ingredients. Chill in icebox.
Serve on bed of crisp lettuce.
This salad is good with cold meat or meat loaf.

title: potato chip squash casserole
directions: In greased casserole, layer squash, soup (undiluted) and crushed potato chips. Repeat layer and top with grated cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown hamburger slowly; add to other ingredients in crock-pot or large kettle.
Preferably cook overnight or until desired taste. Cover with Jiffy muffin mix prepared by directions on box.
Bake at 400° until top browns.

title: pineanna nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 round pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in bananas, nuts, vanilla and pineapple.
Divide batter evenly among pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool ten minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Fill layers and frost side and top of cake with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle pecans on top of cake; cut with sharp knife.
This is also good baked in a long sheet cake pan.

title: mom's holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water; knead until dough is soft. Stretch dough thin.
Tear off a piece at a time.
Poke a hole in the middle; drop into pot of hot lard or grease.
Brown both sides.
Serve hot with honey.

title: karelene's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash cooked sweet potatoes well.
Beat margarine, vanilla, eggs, milk, and sugar.
Pour into a greased baking dish.

title: white chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Stir remainder of ingredients with spinach.
Blend well and refrigerate.

title: crab puffs
directions: Spread on English muffins.
Cut into quarters.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain. Cook noodles. Cook in unsalted water. Drain water from noodles. Combine sausage, noodles, pimento and green pepper. Add milk to soup and heat.
Remove and add grated cheese. Combine with other ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and sliced onion until tender; drain and mash. Add cheese, tomatoes and eggs.
Prepare dressing mix as directed on box and reserve 1/2 cup dry mixture to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Add squash mixture to dressing mixture.
Place in sprayed dish.
Sprinkle on dry dressing.
Bake at 425° (covered) for 30 minutes.
Uncover casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: good old "tater" soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, celery, salt and pepper in 3 quarts water until done.
Cook bacon crisp; drain well.
Break into small pieces; set aside.
Add bacon, milk and margarine to soup.
Serve with hot bread.

title: shrimp quiches
directions: Separate rolls into 2 equal pieces.
Cut in half.
Press into small muffin tins.
Divide shrimp.
Blend all ingredients.
Divide among shells.
Sprinkle cheese over each.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool and freeze.
When you want to serve them, place the frozen quiche on baking sheet and reheat for 15 minutes.
Makes 24 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup strawberry juice for spread.
Mix all dry ingredients and thoroughly combine.
Add food coloring and rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly.

title: coconut cream cake(is a 4 star dessert)
directions: Mix together butter, egg yolks and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix.
Spread into two greased layer cake pans.
Beat 4 egg whites stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually.
Spread over batter in pans. Sprinkle 1/2 to 2/3 cup coconut on each layer.
Bake approximately 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Dredge diced orange candy slices, dates, pecans and coconut with 1/4 cup flour. Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add orange rind. Sift together flour, salt, and soda. Add to butter (sugar) egg mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add candy mixture.
Grease and put wax paper in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out and cool.
One batch also makes 7 mini pans.
Freezes well.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Let cream cheese and Bleu cheese stand at room temperature until softened, then mix together in small bowl.
Add a few dashes of Worcestershire sauce.
Clean celery stalks and cut into 4-inch pieces.
Spread cheese mixture into celery.
Sprinkle with a dash of paprika.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo mixture with lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli; toss lightly and serve.

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Cook, stirring, 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stirring occasionally, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 5 minutes or until desired thickness.
Makes about 3 1/4 cups.
May be stored, tightly covered, in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, stir together soup and sour cream until smooth.
Set aside. Cook onion, chili powder and margarine over medium heat in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in chicken and chilies and 2 tablespoons soup mixture.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and Quaker oats. Blend together well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and put in refrigerator until set.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in punch bowl.

title: cauliflower cabbage salad
directions: Layer ingredients.
Make day before and toss before serving. Keeps 1 week, covered, in refrigerator.

title: coconut-pineapple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square
pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix butter, sugar and coconut; set aside.
Prepare muffin mix as directed on
package
except fold in crushed pineapple. Pour into pan.
Spoon
coconut
mixture
evenly
over
batter. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 9.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and water.
Add can of milk.
Bring to a boil gently for 3 or 4 minutes as it thickens.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter and vanilla.
Serve over ice cream or cake warm or cold.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add beaten eggs; beat well.
Add flour and other dry ingredients including vanilla.
Add chopped apples and nuts.
Mix.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in lemonade; add cold water and cranberry juice.
Place two trays of ice in punch bowl. Pour punch over ice.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving. Serves 25.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; add vanilla.
Roll in balls, then roll in white sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven until lightly browned.

title: tex mex stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans until crumbly. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly golden. Cool.

title: cinnamon nut waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron according to manufacturers directions.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with a rotary beater or mixer until fluffy. Beat in flour, oil, milk, baking powder, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Stir in nuts.
Pour batter onto center of hot waffle iron using the amount suggested by manufacturer.
Bake about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, nutmeg and salt into a bowl. Combine egg yolks, milk and oil.
Pour into flour mixture and beat with a rotary beater or electric mixer just until smooth.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and fold into batter.
Pour batter into greased waffle iron and bake as manufacturer directs. Serve with butter, maple syrup or fruit topping.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until water is absorbed.
In pan combine milk, eggs and sugar.
Cook 35 minutes on low to medium heat.
When done, add vanilla.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet with fork dipped flour and flatten in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Cut bread in half lengthwise making 2 flat slices.
Spread meat mixture on top of bread slices.
Wrap bottom (crust side) in aluminum foil, leaving the top uncovered.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes and apples(pennsylvania dutch)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender; slice in 1/4-inch pieces. Butter baking dish and put a layer of sweet potatoes in bottom, then a layer of apples.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and mace; and dot with butter.
Repeat until dish is filled, having the top layer of apples.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cool.
Cream together 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel layer.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham together in pan.
Add ham. Simmer 45 minutes, stirring to separate and coat ham with sauce. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: mud pudding
directions: You will need a plastic flowerpot without holes, a shovel and silk flowers.

title: turkey or chicken giblet gravy
directions: Melt small amount of butter (margarine) in pan.
Thicken with flour and brown slightly.
Add chopped giblets and broth.
After gravy thickens add eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot over chicken or turkey.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix well; make into 2 rolls.
Store in refrigerator several hours or longer; slice.
Bake at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put margarine in an 8 or 9-inch square baking dish.
Put in oven until melted.
Toss strawberries with 2/3 cup of the sugar and lemon juice.
In separate bowl, mix together all other ingredients.
Pour that mixture
over margarine.
Take strawberries by spoonfuls and drop over mixture. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, chopped onion and salt and drain.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce, water and beans.
Cook until done. Layer in casserole first Fritos or Doritos, then meat mixture, then grated cheese alternately.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Wash beans off.

title: baked country ham
directions: Bake ham for 2 hours in foil.
Mix sugar and honey; baste ham. Top with pineapple slices.
Cook 2 hours or until done.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until softened.
Blend in crab, onion and horseradish sauce.
Spread mixture in a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with sliced almonds.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 3 cups.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and thick.
Slowly add sugar and beat 2 1/2 minutes.
Fold sifted dry ingredients into egg and sugar mixture all at once.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix and butter or margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetables mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until browned.

title: hot cheese ball
directions: Saute the pecans in with butter.
Place the remaining ingredients into a small bowl and mix. Form into balls, then pour mix into a casserole dish. Spread nuts over the top.
Set oven on bake at 350° and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve. Serve with celery sticks, sliced carrots and crackers.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add butter, corn syrup and vanilla. Stir until well blended.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Saute mushrooms, onions and jalapenos.
Melt Velveeta cheese and mix all together. Serve hot with Fritos or nacho chips.

title: "my mama's" elderberry wine
directions: Add water to elderberries.
Let stand 2 days. Boil until soft, then strain through a sieve. To every gallon of liquid, add the sugar, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Cool. When nearly cold, spread a slice of toast with yeast and float on top of liquid.
Let stand 3 to 4 days.
Skim and let stand in keg or crock until through fermenting. Bottle, but "do not" cork too tightly.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Melt together chocolate and margarine; combine sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Mix with chocolate mixture and beat until spreading consistency (may set bowl in ice water).

title: switzerland cheese fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler pan.
Cook very slowly until all is melted; stir constantly.
Put into your fondue pot; keep warm.
Serve with French bread, cut into little squares. Just enjoy.

title: country greens
directions: Have your liquid boiling and add bacon.
Put in greens and cook until done.
Add your vinegar and sugar.
Salt to taste. This works well with green beans also.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13 baking dish (sprayed on bottom with Pam). Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese and chicken.
Half this mixture and put aside in a bowl.
Mix soup and milk in with other half of chicken mixture. Unroll crescents and place 1 tablespoon of dry reserved chicken mixture on crescent and roll up.
Place on a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan; cover with liquid mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until crescents rise and are golden.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to package directions for 6 servings, omitting milk and salt.
Fold in cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, chives and pepper. Spoon into buttered casserole dish and dot with butter. Bake 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mary scott's pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add sugar mixture and blend until smooth.
Add pumpkin and continue to blend until smooth.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° and bake 35 minutes.
Pie is done when knife comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix together and marinate overnight.

title: stuffed lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain off excess fat and stir in flour.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted and mixed in well.
Pour 1/2 sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan and set aside.
Lay a noodle on a work surface and pat dry with paper towel.
Spoon sausage mixture down the center of the noodle.
Roll up and lay seam down in pan with sauce.
Repeat until all noodles are filled.
Spoon remaining sauce over rolls.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of rolls.
Return to oven and bake for another 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: spicy vegetables and sausage
directions: Heat oil to 375° in an electric skillet.
Add onions, green peppers, garlic, tomatoes, zucchini, eggplant, parsley, salt and pepper; saute for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste, wine, sugar, basil, marjoram and seasoned pepper.
Add sausage; cover and cook until sausage is hot and vegetables are crisp-tender (about 5 minutes).
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together.
Add the second set of five ingredients to the first mixture.
Then add 1/2 cup chopped nuts and/or 1/2 cup raisins.
Grease loaf pans.
Bake at 350°.
Bake 2 large loaf pans for 1 hour or 5 small loaves.
Test before hour is up.

title: shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Combine rotini, snow peas, mushrooms, carrot and green onions in large bowl; mix well.
Add dressing; mix well.
Chill for several hours.
Stir in shrimp just before serving.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Press dough in a greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake and let cool. Mix strawberries and glaze.
Pour over baked dough.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop all but 3 slices of chipped beef.
Combine cream cheese, chipped beef and seasonings together.
Roll into a ball.
Cover with remaining chipped beef, wrap in foil and refrigerate.
This is best if made a day ahead.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle cut apples with lemon juice. Combine all ingredients.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil. Add peanut butter. Beat until creamy. Pour over corn flakes and mix. Drop on waxed paper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until middle is firm.

title: pineapple-strawberry shake
directions: Combine all in blender until strawberries are pureed.
Makes 1 (8-ounce) glass.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease generously bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Blend all ingredients on low speed 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans. Cool completely.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as directed on package. Drain macaroni.
Add butter and cheese to macaroni.
Mix until butter and cheese are well mixed.
Add sugar, salt and milk.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake about 30 minutes or until bubbly and light brown.

title: hamburger squash casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger, 1/2 cup chopped onion and the hot peppers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat and add the cheese, half of the soup and half the water.
Mix well together and set aside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 layers.

title: date nut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop or roll loaf in powdered sugar. Cook at 375° for about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: chicken 'n dressing casserole
directions: Layer the deboned chicken in bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix the soup and evaporated milk; pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with chicken broth.
Spread over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake
mix	as
directed in 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool. Mix pudding, cream cheese and canned pineapple.
Spread mixture over
entire cake.	Spread Cool Whip over pudding mix. Sprinkle moist coconut over entire cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream cheese.
Add marshmallow cream.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.
Serve with chunks of pineapple, apple, bananas, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: ham, sausage and bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook lima beans as directed on package. Turn into ungreased 4 1/2-quart casserole.
Add baked beans and kidney beans.

title: perked punch
directions: Put juice in bottom of percolator, spice and sugar in basket. Run automatic normal time.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream sugar and shortening together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk.
Make a heavy smooth paste of cocoa and boiling water; cool slightly and blend well.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour last. Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
If using cookie press, use 1 cup less of flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Use colored sugar on cookies before baking.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients. Add milk and vanilla.

title: golden apple cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 2 tablespoons for frosting.
Combine all ingredients in mixer bowl.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes. Frost between and on top with Maple Flavored Frosting.

title: petit fours
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into a long roll.
Wrap in wax paper; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Remove and slice into cookies.
Fill each one with a favorite jam or preserve.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet after you have folded in half as if making a fried pie. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Place wax paper down.
After each cookie is cooked, roll quickly into powdered sugar.

title: horn-crescents
directions: In large bowl, crumble margarine with 5 cups flour (reserve 1/2 cup for rolling dough), sugar and salt.
Heat milk to lukewarm; dissolve yeast in milk and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well; cover with towel and let rise 20 minutes.
Turn out on floured board.
Start with 1/4 of the dough, using rolling pin and shape into a circle 1/4-inch thick.
Divide into eighths and shape into crescents.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Let rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 32 crescents.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces and place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dissolve pudding mix in cold milk; add ice cream.
Beat until well blended.
Pour over cake.
Do not stir.
Let set. Dissolve jello in boiling water and stir in strawberries.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour over pudding and cake.
Do not stir.
Chill.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Put milk in large bowl. Add beaten eggs and mustard.
Mix well.
Add cubed bread, cheese and sausage. Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and
cocoa in pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1
minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon
drop onto a cookie sheet, lined with foil.	Cool and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add vegetables first and macaroni.
Pour dressing over it. Put in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.

title: gibbons candy
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Drop.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in small amount of margarine until onion is tender.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
Combine celery mixture, broccoli and soup; mix well.
Melt cheese in a different pan, stir in broccoli mixture.
Let cook on slow heat about 5 minutes.
Serve over French bread or use with vegetable sticks.

title: baked onions
directions: Peel onions, boil rapidly 5 minutes; drain and boil in fresh water 5 minutes more.
Drain.
Place in greased baking dish; sprinkle with pepper, sugar and paprika.
Bake at 350° until tender.
You can dot with butter before baking if you like.

title: finger steaks
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients.
Put steak pieces into batter.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Deep fry until brown.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and eggs.
Beat good.
Add pecans, raisins, coconut and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch crust.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: party potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, chives and garlic powder.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve immediately. Dish can be assembled a day ahead and baked just before serving.

title: pizza
directions: Roll out pizza dough and press into pizza pan.
spread sauce over dough and top with favorite topping.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute onion and parsley flakes in butter.
Add sherry, tomato paste, sea salt and a dash of black pepper to onion and parsley. Saute together 3 minutes more.
Add crabmeat and let the heat of the sauteed mixture break up the crab chunks (do not stir excessively) and cook 3 minutes more.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Combine meat, salt, pepper, onion, rice and egg.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into cabbage leaves.
Roll leaves around.
Pour soup and water mixture over cabbage rolls.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in rice, onion and oregano.
Add consomme, mushrooms and water.
Cover with foil. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10; may cut recipe in half.

title: stuffed apple salad
directions: Peel and core apples.
Make a syrup of the water, sugar, food coloring and cinnamon in saucepan.
Add apples, 4 at a time, and cook gently, turning over carefully until done.
Let cool and stuff with a mixture of the remaining ingredients.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg together; add milk and bananas.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt; add to mixture.
Add nuts and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 60 minutes.

title: battletown inn yellow squash
directions: Boil squash in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash. Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter.
Add half and half and cracker crumbs.
Mix with squash and pour into casserole.
Top with additional crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until top browns.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Slice onions.
Use sliced or grated cheese.
Layer potatoes, onions, cheeses, butter, salt and pepper in that order.
Keep adding layers until casserole dish is full or enough for a meal.
Cover dish.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: batman cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix brown sugar and margarine together. Add granulated sugar, eggs, flour, and vanilla.
Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 X 12 X 2 greased pan.
Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.
Let cool, cut into squares, roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour
cream together.
Stir in Jell-O. Fold in fruit cocktail.
Add pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: katie's stuff
directions: In Ziploc bag, crush Oreo cookies.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: underground ham casserole
directions: Combine ham, oleo, onion and Worcestershire sauce and cook until onions are soft.
Place in bottom of roaster.
In a saucepan heat together soup, milk and cheese until cheese melts.
Pour over cooked noodles and ham mixture.
Mash potatoes; add sour cream and some milk.
Spread over top of mixture and sprinkle crumbled bacon over top.
Bake 20 minutes.
The mushroom and cheese mixture comes to the top when done.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti with cold water.
Pour 1 (16 ounce) bottle Zesty Italian dressing over mixture.
Add 3 tablespoons Salad Supreme.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart microwave bowl and mix good. Cook 4 minutes on High. Stir. Cook 4 more minutes on High. Remove and add the butter and vanilla.
Put back into microwave oven and cook 2 minutes on High.
Take out and add the baking soda.
Quickly stir until light and foamy.
Pour out on foil paper on kitchen counter.
Cool, then break into small pieces. Store in covered container.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together.
Add lemonade and mix.
Pour into crust and chill a couple of hours.

title: potpourri to simmer
directions: In a large glass jar, cover all the ingredients with heated white vinegar.
Cover.
Let the mixture sit for approximately one week.
Use in potpourri hot pots or simmer on top of your range. Gives a wonderful aroma!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter
dish and add mixture of beans and soup.
Cover. Place in
preheated 400°oven for 10 minutes until the mixture bubbles. Reduce heat to 300° for 20 minutes.
Add onion rings and cook 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Boil potatoes; drain and peel.
Add butter.
Beat well.
Mix in sugar, eggs, milk and flavorings and spices.
Pour in pie crust (use deep), then bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvres
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add margarine, cheese, onion and spinach.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Cut into small squares
or use small muffin tins.
Freezes well.

title: creamy rice and tomatoes
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Stir in cheese and tomatoes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli and cauliflower florets in a large bowl.
Peel one tomato and cut up.
Crumble bacon up in bowl.
Mix Miracle Whip and lemon juice.
Toss on vegetables and chill. Serve.

title: marinated vegetable soup
directions: Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler. While waiting, measure flour and sugar.
Mix together, then add beaten eggs, then melted butter and chocolate.
Mix all together.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Pour into two 8-inch square pans. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Butter
casserole dish or spray with Pam.
Peel squash; cut in chunks.
Cook, drain and mash.
Add next 8 ingredients to squash mix.
Melt oleo.
Mix cracker crumbs with oleo.
Add some to mixture.
Pour in casserole and sprinkle rest on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: roast suckling pig
directions: Stuff the pig, then sew up the opening with fine string. Brush entire surface with oil or melted butter and wrap in several folds of well-greased grease-proof paper. Draw the legs well back and tie in a good shape.
Roast in moderate oven (350°) according to size, allowing 25 minutes per pound and 25 minutes over.
Baste every 1/2 hour.

title: easy brown sugar pie
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add brown sugar.
Add eggs and then add milk and vanilla.
Mix by hand until smooth.
Pour into 2 unbaked pastry shells. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine remaining ingredients well. Place in greased casserole dish and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cover with crushed crackers and grated cheese.
Brown and let cheese melt.

title: chocolate cookies(cookie bar)
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan with marshmallows.
In saucepan, melt oleo, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Once melted, add peanuts.
Pour mixture over top of marshmallows, then refrigerate.

title: pizza on a bun
directions: Brown sausage.
Let simmer sausage and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle in oregano.
Grate cheese.
Serve sauce on hamburger buns and top with grated cheese.
Put in oven and broil long enough to melt cheese and brown slightly.

title: luann's apple pie
directions: Fill uncooked pie crust with sliced apples.
Mix juice concentrate and cornstarch and pour over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put top crust on and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Tastes best the next day.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix 2 c. sugar, butter, and then add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk, nuts and raisins.
Take half of batter and pour into pans.
Then put spices in the other half batter and bake until firm at 350°.

title: corn and swiss cheese bake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into 4 lightly greased custard cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish if desired.

title: cinnamon fluff
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients together.
After in the pan, cover top with brown sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
A quick breakfast treat.

title: spaghetti and crabs
directions: Pour olive oil to cover bottom of stock pot.
Heat oil and lightly brown the garlic and parsley.
Saute the crabs with lid on the pot until they turn pink (about 20 minutes).
Shake the pot to move the crabs around inside the pot.
Don't try to stir them while you're cooking them.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours (the longer, the better).
Remove crabs into side bowl.
Cook spaghetti and serve with the sauce and crabs on the side.
It's messy to eat, but delicious!

title: creamy skillet corn
directions: Put corn in skillet with butter, cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes or until mixture is fairly thick and corn is tender.
Serve sprinkled with paprika. Makes 4 servings.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, 2 cups cold water and pineapple in blender. Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Mix jello and 2 cups boiling water in casserole dish until mixture is ropey.
Add grapes, celery, pecans and cranberry mixture.
Add Equal to taste, usually 12 packages.

title: parsley buttered potatoes
directions: Peel, quarter and wash potatoes.
Boil potatoes to tender bite; drain.
Clean and chop parsley, medium to fine.
Melt butter and add parsley with salt.
Pour parsley butter sauce over drained potatoes and serve.

title: *meatball soup 1
directions: Mix all ingredients except parsley and form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll into chopped parsley.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepot.
Place meatballs in pot and carefully add enough water or chicken broth to cover and cook for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a pot, boil squash, celery, onions, butter and water for 5 minutes. Then combine with cracker crumbs, beaten eggs and grated cheese. Pour into lightly buttered baking dish; sprinkle on topping. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat the eggs well and add to creamed mixture.
Sift and add to previous mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan, 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: quick jello salad
directions: Let Cool Whip soften completely.
In a large bowl, mix the Cool Whip, cottage cheese, Jell-O and fruit.
Let sit 15 minutes in the refrigerator.
Serve.

title: carrot cake with molasses(low-fat dessert)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 13 x 9-inch baking pan with foil. Coat with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Beat sugar, pineapple, oil and vanilla in mixer bowl until smooth.
Beat in dry ingredients until just combined.
Stir in carrots.
Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl to a stiff peak. Fold into carrot mixture in 2 batches.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 40 minutes.
Spread icing on cooled cake.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at the time. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 250 degrees for 2 hours. Let cool in pan until half cool.

title: peanut butter crisscross cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
(If using self-rising flour, leave out soda, salt and baking powder.) Add this to first mixture with vanilla.
Chill.
Then form into balls the size of a small walnut.
Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross on each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in moderate oven at 375°.
These cookies are rich and burn easily, so watch your oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into loaf.
Top with ketchup and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn flakes snacks
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil. Add peanut butter and let melt. Pour over corn flakes. Drop by tablespoonful onto wax paper or buttered cookie sheet.

title: sugar free cherry pie
directions: Mix cherries, flour, Sweet 'N Low and margarine together. Place in one crust.
Place second crust over the top and seal edges.
Cut vent holes in top crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lefsa
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add extra flour if dough is sticky. Roll out paper thin.
Fry as you would fry pancakes.

title: triple layer dessert
directions: Put cookies in blender and crumb.
Put 1/2 cup aside.
Mix melted margarine and cookies.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat together the first four ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
This will be like a cake batter.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Invert onto cotton towel sprinkled with powdered sugar and cool.

title: salsa fries (steak)
directions: Cut steak into thin slices.
Put a little oil in a skillet. Heat to medium-low. Drain oil.
Add one jar of salsa. Cover. Turn heat to low.
Simmer for about 30 minutes or until tender.

title: german caramel bars
directions: Combine cake mix, evaporated milk and oil.
Blend well
and spread one half in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Meanwhile, unwrap candy and combine with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Melt in double boiler or microwave. Pour over baked dough.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Carefully spread remaining dough over caramel.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove bones and skin and cut into small pieces.
Reserve 2 cups of broth.
Mix dressing with melted butter.
Spread 1/2 dressing mixture into bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Spread lay of chicken over dressing.
Mix 2 cups of reserved broth with chicken soup and pour over chicken.
Mix celery soup with remaining broth and pour over chicken.
Spread remainder of dressing on top.
Bake at 400 degrees until brown (approx. 30 min.).

title: country style corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into ungreased pan or casserole.
Bake about 30 minutes; top with cheese and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Peel and quarter potato.
Boil in small saucepan as for mashed potatoes.
When tender, remove from stove; drain off water and mash potato with a fork.
Pour in enough powdered sugar to make dough like.
Remove mixture and place on flat powdered sugar surface to roll with a rolling pin.
Roll into a thin rectangle. Spread peanut butter on top of rectangle and roll dough jelly roll style, starting at narrow end.
Slice into pieces 1/2-inch wide. Let stand until dry.
Amount will vary, depending on size of potato and thickness of slices.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk or cream (milk is better) and vanilla together until it becomes like a syrup and forms a ball in cold water.
Add peanut butter.
Beat until thick and begins to harden.
Spread in buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: top crust for fruit pie
directions: Use with apple, pear, peach, cherry or any kind of berry pie.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spread cottage cheese in greased 9-inch pie plate. Cook ground beef; drain. Stir in 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, salt, oregano and tomato paste; spoon over cottage cheese. Stir milk, baking mix and eggs with fork until blended. Pour into baking dish. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 1 or 2 minutes or until melted. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dip and coat chicken breasts in flour.
Put oil in frying pan and saute chicken lightly on both sides.
Sprinkle each side with garlic powder.
In a casserole pan, pour Marsala wine and bouillon mixture.
Place sauteed chicken and remaining flour in wine and bouillon combination.
Add mushrooms to top of chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with seasoned rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Precook squash and onion until just tender.
Stir in 1 can undiluted mushroom soup, 2 eggs, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Put in oiled casserole dish and bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.
Return to oven to melt cheese and brown crumbs.

title: mom's best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square pan; set aside.
In bowl, combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
In large bowl, whisk egg whites, egg, sugar, applesauce, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until just blended; do not over mix.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts if desired.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Place pan on a wire rack.
Let cool 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Place one layer on top of the other in order given in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be served with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter candy squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix thoroughly with hands and press into a 9 x 13-inch or slightly larger pan.

Pack down hard. Melt 1/2 stick margarine, chocolate chips and Crisco together in pan on stove or in bowl in microwave and pour/spread quickly and smoothly over the top of the pan of peanut butter mixture.
Cool in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: mocha icing
directions: Heat coffee until boiling.
Add coffee to butter and cream in mixing bowl and mix until thoroughly blended.
Add vanilla extract and salt.
Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together and blend into coffee mixture gradually until of right consistency to spread.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook fat, onion, garlic and mushrooms for 10 minutes.
Add flour; stir until blended.
Add broth; stir until thick.
Add chicken, tomatoes and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Arrange layer of chicken and spaghetti.
Put crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut pie (makes own crust)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, butter and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 well buttered pie pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Butter sides of 2-quart kettle.
Add first 3 ingredients.
Heat slowly to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add vinegar (white).
Cook to light crack stage, 268°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and sift in soda.
Stir to mix.
Turn out on buttered plate (do not scrape). Turn edges to center.
With buttered fingers, pull as warm as you can handle.
Cut in quarters.
Pull and clip with shears.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: grilled ham and chicken slices
directions: Rub the exterior and the cavity of the chicken with the first 4 ingredients and allow to stand for 1 hour.
Place the chicken, breast side up, on a heatproof platter.
Steam over high heat for 20 minutes. Remove the chicken. Retain the broth. Allow the chicken to cool, then bone.
Cut the chicken meat into pieces 2-inches wide and 1-inch thick.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You will also need 24 cupcake liners.

title: garlic dip
directions: Cream the Philadelphia cream cheese with Pet milk until soupy consistency. Squeeze garlic into mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Additional Pet milk can be added if too thick. Serve with potato chips.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter; add sugars and eggs.
Beat well.
Mix in flour mixture.
Gradually stir in oats. Add coconut and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: hot apricot punch
directions: Heat, but do not boil, in crock-pot.
Serve warm.

title: berry muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients, reserving 2 tablespoons flour for dredging the berries.
Beat egg slightly, add milk and gradually the dry ingredients.
Add melted butter.
Fold in berries to coat well with flour.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake in hot oven.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown. Serve at once.

title: christmas bread
directions: Thaw and soften dough.
In a small mixing bowl, cream together the powdered sugar and butter.
Mix in nuts, cherries, raisins and lemon extract.
Set aside.
Roll dough into a 14x8 inch rectangle.
Spread filling to within 1 inch of edge. Beginning from the longest side, roll dough in jelly roll fashion. Pinch to seal seam.
Place on a greased baking sheet with seam side down.
Cut slashes alternately to the right and the left. Turn each slice on its side to show the filling.
Cover, let rise until doubled in size.
Bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool on a wire rack.
If desired, garnish with red and green candied cherries.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in oil in large Dutch oven until tender.
Add tomatoes and next 3 ingredients.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat; add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a crock-pot. Serve with chips.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into pieces.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes in salted water. Drain.
Butter a casserole dish.
Layer cabbage, chopped onion, cream of mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Keep layering until casserole is full.
Top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. To serve, mix 2 tablespoons of cocoa mixture with 8 ounces of hot water, more or less to suit taste.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar with a tight lid.
Let stand several hours.
Remove garlic.
Shake well before using.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring pineapple (juice, too) to boiling.
Add Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
Remove from heat and cool a few minutes, then add cranberry sauce, apples and nuts.
Let set at room temperature until cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into an oblong dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, pumpkin, salt and vanilla.
Beat well; add melted butter and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell, unbaked.
Arrange pecans on top attractively.
Bake 45 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in saucepan and remove from heat.
Stir in the oats, flour, corn syrup, milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to shortening, sugar and egg mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add 2 cups oats.
Add 1 cup raisins.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: egg and sausage or bacon breakfast casserole
directions: Blend well and put in flat baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot slaw
directions: Mix together and serve cold.

title: pineapple-rhubarb mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine rhubarb, sugar and water.
Cover and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly, reserving syrup.
Add water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Heat to boiling, add gelatin and stir to dissolved.
Add lemon juice. Cool.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in rhubarb and pineapple. Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on greens. Garnish with pineapple.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen onion rings
directions: Take a firm onion and slice thick slices; separate into rings. Blanch a few rings at a time in boiling water for 15 seconds.
Cool quickly in ice water; drain.
Roll rings separate.
Roll in flour, dip in milk and roll one more time in a mixture of half pancake mix and half cornmeal.
Freeze on cookie sheet and pack in single layers.
Take out as many as you like at a time.
While still frozen, fry in fat until lightly browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Start with 2 eggs and mix in sour cream.
Add both cans of corn, not drained.
Mix in cornbread mix and sugar.
Mix well. Pour into greased baking dish; sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes, until done.

title: pineapple delight dessert
directions: Crumbled 1/2 of the cake in the bottom of a Pyrex dish (size as needed).
Layer 1/2 of the crushed pineapple over the cake crumbs. Repeat.
Cover well with Cool Whip.
Decorate with whole pecans and cherries (generously).
Leave overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda, sugar and salt.
Combine eggs, water, oil and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients slowly to the egg combination.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake in 3 loaf pans at 350° until middle springs back.

title: supper in a skillet
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg, onion and salt. Shape into meatballs. Brown in skillet. Drain off fat drippings. Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat 20 minutes or until meat is done, stirring occasionally. If desired, some cheese may be added. Makes about 4 servings.

title: porky pine meatballs
directions: Cook rice separately; drain and rinse.
Mix all ingredients, except tomato soup and water.
Roll mixture into balls.
Combine soup and water in crock-pot or slow cooker.
Add meat balls and cook until meat is thoroughly cooked.
You can thicken the soup mixture and serve with meatballs.
Makes about 10 to 12 meatballs.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon yogurt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients at low speed, then mix at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Bake in greased Bundt pan in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients, except raisins; mix well.
Bake in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven.
Stir in raisins.
Spread onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Store in refrigerator when cooled.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Place in serving dish, layered as listed.
Serve with Fritos corn chips.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Defrost frozen bread. Roll out on floured surface to 18-inches long x 6-inches wide.
Spread tomato paste evenly.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Place mixture down center of bread.
Pull up sides and pinch together to seal.
Place on greased cookie sheet in horseshoe fashion.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve with salad. Freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix altogether and roll in a ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in a small amount of hot water.
Add pineapple juice, sugar and enough water to make one gallon of punch.
Add ginger ale right before serving.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar together, then add the beer.
Mix well; pour into well-greased bread pan.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in cooled, melted chocolate or cocoa mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition at high speed.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour into a cooled, baked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: pink lima beans
directions: Soak beans over night.	Put beans in large crock pot and cover with water.
Add onions and sausage.	Cook on low heat while at work.
You can also eat this over rice.	Great for winter time.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Put 1/2 cup egg nog into saucepan; add unflavored gelatin. Bring to a boil and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Into bowl, pour 1 1/2 cups egg nog (cold) and rum.
Pour hot egg nog into cold egg nog; place in refrigerator to thicken.
When thickened, fold in heavy cream and pour into pie shell.
Place in refrigerator until needed.

title: peach cake
directions: Sprinkle cake mix in 9x13 cake pan.
Cover with peaches and juice.
Cover well with coconut and melted butter.
Bake 350 degrees until done.

title: whole wheat pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast and honey in water.
Mix in 2 cups bread flour and salt.
Add olive oil and blend 30 seconds.
Gradually add whole wheat flour until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise in a greased bowl until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down.
Re-cover and let rice another 45 minutes.

title: spinach rockefeller a la kolodner(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all other ingredients, except tomatoes.
Add spinach and mix well.
Grease 2-quart casserole and make 2 layers of tomatoes on bottom.
Pour spinach on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
(May be assembled the day before and baked on the day needed.)

title: ono ono cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Melt butter and add gradually to the dry ingredients.
Stir in milk and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet-and-sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set both aside.
Brown pork in oil in a large skillet; stir in water.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour, or until tender.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium bowl; stir in reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Add to pork and cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion; toss lightly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jello, sugar and water; bring to rolling boil. Mix cornstarch and sufficient amount of water and mix well. Add slowly to boiling mixture. Boil hard; cool.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt, pineapple, banana pieces and enough red color to give pink tint.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer carrots, pepper and onion in bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour marinade over vegetables and allow to set overnight.
Will keep for 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and remove meat from bone in small chunks.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix milk with canned soups and pour over chicken.
Pour chicken broth over stuffing mix and mix well.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fantastic chuck roast
directions: Place meat in baking dish.
Use spatula to spread soup over top and sides of meat.
Press onions into soup layer and arrange mushrooms around edges of pan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Don't peek!
Let sit for 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually, and blend in applesauce to which soda has been added.
Stir in raisins.
Add sifted dry ingredients and blend until smooth.
Turn into a greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: frances' lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion; add sugar, tomato paste and 2 cups of water.
Pour in spaghetti mix; stir well and simmer.
(May need to add more water if beef mixture is too thick.) In saucepan, pour 1/4 cup of
milk over cream cheese and stir over medium heat until well blended.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix jello with 3/4 cup boiling water and 1/2 cold water. Stir together and set aside.

title: easy banana cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, oil, water, bananas and baking soda.
Blend at low speed until moistened, then mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until done.

title: the chocolate cake(nancy barr, troy, alabama)
directions: Dissolve soda in water; mix other ingredients.
Add water. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add food coloring to make different colors.
Store in plastic containers to keep soft.

title: 10-minute pizza
directions: Split muffins and toast.
Layer cheese, tomato sauce and oil on each.
Season to taste.
Top with sprinkle of Parmesan cheese. Place on cookie sheet and place in 450° oven.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes until ingredients are hot and cheese melts.

title: sausage-shrimp jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage and bacon, stirring frequently.
Remove and drain all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onions and green pepper; cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Add parsley, bacon, sausage, garlic and seasonings; mix well.
Place shrimp over mixture.
Do not stir.
Pour rice over shrimp.
Add water to barely cover rice.
Do not stir. Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 30 minutes.
Remove cover.
Reduce heat and continue heating 15 minutes to dry jambalaya.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in greased heavy 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook covered for 2 to 3 minutes or until steam washes sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Cook uncovered to 234 to 240° on candy thermometer or the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch dish.
Let stand until firm.

title: angel kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and dash of salt.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by well-rounded teaspoonfuls (about 2 bites) onto ungreased foil-lined cookie sheet.
Place cookie sheet in preheated oven (350°).
Turn oven off immediately.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Add shrimp, salt, pepper and parsley. Cook over medium to high heat, stirring constantly, until shrimp are pink, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press
crescent
rolls in pan.	Bake until golden brown (approximately 10 minutes) at 425°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cut leftover cooked meat into cubes and any leftover veggies. Mix altogether with gravy sufficient to moisten.
Add onion and seasonings.
Place in a deep baking dish and cover with well seasoned mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: quail
directions: Wash and pat dry quail (whole).
Stuff each one with raw oysters.
Season with Worcestershire sauce.
Place in a greased roaster.
Cover each quail with half strip of bacon, covering all exposed areas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or golden brown and thigh juice runs clear with knife.
Serve with milk gravy and grits.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in medium saucepan.
Stir over medium-high heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil; boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Quickly stir in oatmeal and nuts. Stir well and quickly spoon out onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken. Layer in pan with heavy-duty foil. Salt and pepper. Put light layer of Bertolli olive oil over it. Put 1/4 cup of water. Make tinfoil tent sealed on each end. Bake at 375° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil, sugar and powdered sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well and add vanilla and lemon juice.
Form in tiny balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend the ingredients together in a bowl; press firmly into the bottom and part way up the sides of a 9-inch spring pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine
mustard and flour;
add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour in greased pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese
on top and red pepper (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or longer.

title: heavenly pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks.
Add sugar; fold in baking powder and cracker crumbs.
Add vanilla and pecans. Turn into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit salt.
If using instantized flour, stir 2 tablespoons milk into butter mixture.

title: quick crawfish jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add green pepper, celery and onions.
Cook over medium heat until tender, but not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except crawfish.
Bring to a boil.
Stir once or twice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Mixture should be slightly moist.
Stir in crawfish and cook until thoroughly heated, about 2 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potpourri
directions: Place all ingredients in a large jar and cover with heated white vinegar.
Let the jar sit for about a week, then place some of the potpourri in a simmering pot.

title: peanut butter balls dipped in white chocolate
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, vanilla and peanut butter together well and roll into spoon size balls.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine milk, 1/2 cup of butter, sugar and salt in saucepan. Heat until butter is melted.
Cool.
Stir in yeast until dissolved.
Place flour in a large bowl.
Make a well in flour and pour in liquid.
Stir until blended.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk (1 1/2 hours).
Turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Roll 1/2 inch thick; cut into 3-inch squares.
Dip each square in remaining butter and layer in tube or Bundt pan; let rise 3/4 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Put cut apples and sugar in a blue granite canner and put in a 300° to 350° oven overnight or for 6 to 8 hours.
When done, run through colander and add cinnamon or spices to suit taste.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.
Put in pint jars and pressure to 5 pounds.
Cool and store.
It's so simple to make and uses up lots of drop apples.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes uncovered.

title: soft pumpkin drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel. Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool and frost with Vanilla Frosting.

title: white trash
directions: Mix raisins, peanuts, graham crackers and cereal together. In a separate bowl, mix margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Let partially set.
When jello mixture is partially firm, spread on top of cheese layer and chill thoroughly.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding nuts last, and bake, in a Bundt pan for 1 hour, in a 325° oven.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed. Pour half of batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels with butter and condensed milk. Pour over cake and sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans. Pour rest of batter on top and bake another 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian christmas punch
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Chill.
Just before serving add orange soda and ice.
Serves 30.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 hours.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.

title: cathy's noodle kugel
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Place into well-greased, shallow, heavy casserole or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 3/4 to one hour, until cooked.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12 as side dish.
It's a holiday favorite.

title: cream cheese lemon pie
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix in 1/3 cup lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla; mix well.
Put in pie crust.
Chill about 2 hours, then serve.

title: rainbow pudding
directions: You will also need 8 (4-ounce) baby food jars.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Combine crushed cookies and 1/2 cup butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Spread ice cream on crusts and freeze.

title: lemon danish rolls
directions: Let dough thaw until pliable (dough can be thawed overnight in the refrigerator or thawed in microwave on Low for 6 minutes each loaf).
Divide each loaf of thawed bread dough into 8 pieces. Gently shape each piece into a rope, 15 inches long.
Hold one end of each rope in place and wind dough around loosely to form a coil; tuck end firmly underneath.
Place on greased baking sheets about 2 inches apart.
Brush with melted butter or margarine and let rise in warm place for 1 to 2 hours or until doubled in size.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine all the first 4 ingredients and let set until very firm.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix together.
Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sundae pie
directions: First
Layer:
Mix
together
the
flour,
melted oleo, chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: Mix liquid and dry ingredients separately. Dip pork chops into liquid, then roll in dry mix. Fry in deep hot fat until both sides are brown. Remove and put in a shallow baking dish.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Dilute the cans of soup with 1 can of water.
Mix chicken, rice and soups together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle the 1 cup bread crumbs on top and dot with margarine/butter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: apricot nectar mold
directions: Bring nectar to a boil and dissolve Jell-O.
Add oranges and their juice.
Place in mold.
Serve with a topping of sour cream sweetened with sugar and vanilla to taste.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix fruit, coconut and marshmallows with yogurt and Cool Whip or whipped cream which have been combined together.
Maraschino cherries may be added as garnish.

title: grampa dawson's old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Put all into casserole in 300° oven.
Stir often until last half hour.
Let it form a crust and brown last half hour.
Bake at least 1 hour or more until done.

title: orange julius
directions: Put in Osterizer.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: miracle meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch and water until clear; cool.
Beat egg whites and sugar until foamy.
Add cornstarch mixture and beat stiff. Add vanilla.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor until well blended. Serve with plain crackers or vegetables.
Best when made the day before and left in the fridge overnight before using.

title: oatmeal cake
