directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water together in a bowl and set aside for about 20 min.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add soggy oatmeal and mix 3 min.
Pour into greased and floured 9 by 13 in. cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(If you want to add a choc. crust, add a bag of choc. chips to batter and then bake.)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Add all ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Activate yeast in warm water.
In a large mixing bowl, cut flour and baking soda with shortening, add buttermilk and sugar. Add activated yeast and knead well.
Stores in refrigerator well.

title: pizza in a pot
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Boil noodles until they start to soften (they will finish cooking in the crock-pot). Combine meat, noodles, and spaghetti sauce in a large bowl.
Layer this mixture with the two cheeses and pepperoni in a crock pot. The top layer will be the cheeses and pepperoni.
Warm in the crock pot until the cheese is completely melted (2-3 hours).

title: spanish rice(for big recipe)
directions: *Increase amount of hamburger for larger recipes.
The original recipe did not list quantities of ingredients.

title: pizza
directions: Heat oil in saucepan and saute garlic.
When brown, add tomatoes and the rest of the sauce ingredients together.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare dough in pizza pans as for thick pizza but
use less dough for each pizza and roll dough out very thin.
Complete
all
pizzas
and let rest about 10 minutes before putting on the sauce.
Place about 1/2 to 3/4 cup sauce
on each pizza.
Arrange desired toppings on pizza, ending with
a little olive oil, salt and pepper.
Cook for
about
25 to 30 minutes.
Mozzarella, Provolone and white Cheddar can
be added the last 5 minutes.
Sauce makes 5 to 6 pizzas.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry the ground beef and minced onion. Drain off any grease. Add the salt, brown sugar, pork and beans and barbecue sauce. Bring to a boil.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Cut the biscuits in half.
Place the biscuits, cut side down, around the casserole.
Sprinkle with the grated cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place a single layer of whole graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with one-half of the pudding mixture.
Place another layer of graham crackers and cover with rest of pudding.
Place another layer of crackers on pudding. Melt oleo and chocolate together; remove from burner.
Add corn syrup, vanilla, powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons milk.
Mix and pour over last graham cracker layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: applesauce cake with caramel icing
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients. In a large bowl, combine sugar and oil until well blended.

Stir in warm applesauce and blend thoroughly. Add dry ingredients, blending well. Stir in raisins and walnuts. Bake in Bundt pan about 25 minutes at 350°, then increase temperature to 375° and bake 1 hour longer. Test cake's doneness with a knife inserted into the middle of cake. If doughy, bake a little longer.

title: quickie coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend 2 minutes.
Pour into buttered pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple honey crisp
directions: Spread sliced apples in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.
Pour honey over all.
Into a bowl put the flour, brown sugar, salt and nuts.
Work in the butter as for biscuits, making a crumbly mixture.
Spread crumbs evenly over the apples and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Crust should be brown.
Serve warm with plain cream or whipped cream with a dash of cinnamon.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop or grind peppers and onions.
Food processor works great.

title: chicken with wine
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4-inches.
Salt and pepper.
Dip in beaten eggs, then in crumbs.
Fry in oil, lightly browning both sides.
Remove and place in greased casserole.
Melt margarine. Add flour to make a smooth paste.
Add milk slowly; cook until thick.
Remove and add wine.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle on 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Line bottom of 9x13 in

cake pan with graham crackers. Mix pudding according to pkg directions. Add cool whip to pudding and spread half of mixture on top of crackers. Add another layer of crackers and other half of filling. Top with blueberry filling. Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: cereal
directions: Put Dinosaurs in bowl; put a little bit of milk and mix it.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients 1 1/2 minutes.
Add rest and drop by spoonfuls.
Let it chill overnight.

title: old fashioned pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add salt and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add margarine and beat again.
Add vanilla, corn syrup, and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Bring milk and butter to boiling stage.
Add to eggs and sugar.
Stir well.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cook until firm.

title: belgium salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil in saucepan and heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and cool.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetable.
Chill before serving.

title: suicide cookies
directions: Using a cookie sheet with an edge, spread margarine evenly over the bottom.
Spread the remaining ingredients, one at a time, in several layers, making sure there is as much along sides as in the middle.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars after cooling down.

title: lemon lime salad
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Dissolve jello and marshmallows in boiling water.
Chill until slightly congealed.

title: lemon filling for cake
directions: Combine egg and sugar in saucepan.
Blend well, then add lemon juice and butter.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool before using.
This is a very good filling to put between white cake layers.
This filling really should be made the day before it's going to be used.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
It will be nice and thick.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend cake mix with pudding mix, water, eggs and oil.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Completely cool before frosting.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and corn syrup in 3-qt bowl.
Mix until sugar dissolves.
Microwave 5 minutes on high.
Stir well. Microwave 7 minutes on high while cooking syrup.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
When ready, pour syrup very slowly into egg whites heating all of the time.
Add vanilla.
Beat until loses gloss (about 8 minutes).
Fold in nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: veal paprikas
directions: Wash the meat and cut it into large squares.
Put in pan two tablespoons of fat and heat.
Dice the onions finely and dip into fat, stirring until soft.
Now add two teaspoons of red paprika pepper and stir once.
Salt.
Put in the meat, together with the fresh tomatoes (or one or two teaspoons of puree if fresh tomatoes are not available).
Add a little water, barely covering the meat and stew under lid, stirring from time to time.
If necessary, add a small amount of water again until meat is tender.
Cream may be used before serving, according to taste.
May use turkey slices, uncooked.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Chop other vegetables fine.
(I put them through blender).
Mix spices, sugar, flour, salt and vinegar. Add chopped vegetables and corn.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal at once.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes just to assure sealing.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and water; set aside.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and roll out on floured surface; cut as biscuits. Allow to rise in a warm dark place.
Bake at 450° until golden. May be kept in refrigerator for up to a week.

title: chix-rice casserole(quick and easy)
directions: Put chicken on top of rice.
Pour soup and broth over mixture. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with cheese and noodles. Put back in oven long enough for cheese to melt.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Chop potatoes and cook.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put oleo, sour cream and celery soup in a saucepan.
Stir until oleo is melted.
Mix with potatoes.
Mix in onion and cheese.
Put some cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown turkey and onion in Dutch oven.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer (low) until rice is tender and most of liquid is cooked out, approximately 30 minutes.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer, but do not boil.
Serve hot or refrigerate and heat in microwave as needed.
We always have this on hand at Christmastime.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine cheeses and layer 1/2 in 9 x 9-inch dish. Cover with chilies.
Mix eggs, milk and flour.
Pour over cheese.
Pour on the remainder of the cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: jam cake
directions: Save out 2 egg whites for icing.
Beat 4 egg whites and fold into cake batter last.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add Rotel, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and green chiles. Picante sauce can be substituted for chilies.
Mix well.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of the meat sauce.
Cover with pieces of the corn tortillas, quarter or eighths.
Repeat until all meat sauce is used.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350.

title: worlds greatest chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Add water chestnuts, olives, salt, pepper, garlic salt, paprika and celery seed; mix well. Refrigerate. Serves 3-4.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat in skillet; add taco seasoning and prepare as directed on package.
Next, add sauce and cook until thick.
Put on top of crushed chips, topped with tossed salad made with your favorite vegetables.
Top with Italian dressing and grated cheese.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, syrup and salt; boil for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; mix well.
Pour over 1 pan of popcorn.
Mix well.

title: date log cookie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, dates and eggs in saucepan.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add Rice Krispies.
Shape into round balls; roll in chopped nuts.
No baking.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until golden brown. Mix oleo and garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: chocolate chip cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a preheated oven for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: moravian cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, lard and butter.
Add molasses, soda and spices.
Add all flour possible to make a stiff dough.
Use remainder of flour for rolling.
Cover and let stand overnight in cold place.
The next day, roll out very, very thin using a heavy cloth on board and a thin cloth around rolling pin; the thinner, the better.
Cut in various shapes.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes on well-greased cookie sheet.

title: ricotta doughnuts
directions: Soften Ricotta cheese.	Beat the eggs into the Ricotta. Add sugar, vanilla,
flour, salt and baking powder;
mix well. Heat oil.
Place
dough by teaspoonfuls in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown
(approximately
3 minutes).	Remove with slotted spoon. Drain on paper towels.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pork chop casserole ii
directions: Brown chops quickly.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Top with potatoes and add a layer of cheese.
Mix soup with water and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: quick pecan drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine cake mix, butter, egg and milk; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar
and
flour
in
a large bowl (do not use electric mixer).
In double boiler combine and bring to a boil the margarine,	cocoa, oil and water.
Pour mixture over sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate filled bonbons(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using mixer, cream the shortening and both sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and extracts; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix until blended.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Press each ball around a kiss so kiss is completely enclosed (you should not see the kiss).
Bake for 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack. Frost or decorate as desired.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Saute onion in butter in skillet until golden brown.
Add mushrooms, broccoli and tomato.
Cook for 4 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, salt and oregano.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Mix in cheese.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and dip balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper and let dry.
Makes 100 to 150 balls.

title: potato casserole(microwave magic)
directions: Defrost hash browns 10 minutes in dish you plan to use.
Mix all ingredients with hash browns.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and mix with 1 1/2 cups crushed cornflakes.
Put on top of potatoes. Cook 15 minutes in microwave.

title: german cabbage bake
directions: Cut
cabbage
into
wedges, then pieces and steam until just cooked.
Brown onion in the butter (or margarine) and add bread crumbs; mix well.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Butter the sides and bottom of 2 x 8-inch casserole dish. Boil macaroni in salted water for 10 minutes; then drain.
Pour 1/2 elbow macaroni in bottom of dish.

Put layer of sliced cheese on top of that and 1/2 stick of butter (in chunks) on that. Repeat this process with the rest of the macaroni and butter. Pour milk into casserole until it comes about 3/4-inch to the top of the dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut kiss me cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with the milk and coconut.
Continue beating.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into a lightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Add cheese to Basic Meat Loaf recipe. Cut peppers in halves and stuff with meat mixture.
Pour Marinara Sauce over them and bake 1 hour.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Add pineapple and refrigerate in a 9 x 12-inch pan until mixture starts to set.
Press marshmallows into top and set aside.

title: stir-fry spaghetti
directions: In electric skillet, brown chicken after it is cut up.
Add Chinese vegetables and oil, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots; cover.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti.
When spaghetti is done, drain off.
Add to chicken and vegetables.
Add soy sauce.
Serve hot.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. Beat eggs, add milk. Add salt & mustard. Add cubed bread and stir. Add cheese and sausage. Put in 9x11 baking dish. Refrierate over night.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buried burgers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Heat on stove.
You can do burgers on grill or in fry pan on stove.
Brown them a little on each side.
Then lay in crock-pot and pour above mixture over them, put on low and let cook in sauce for about 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch, 1 box berries and food coloring.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove and add other box of berries and a lump of butter.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: dip for fruits
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Great for apples, bananas, kiwi, strawberries, grapes and oranges.

title: cocoa no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter together.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Ready to eat in 5 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli in ungreased pan.
Put broccoli in bottom.
Beat soup and milk until smooth with a fork; pour over broccoli. Sprinkle cheese over that.
Mix butter and Bisquick with fork. Pour over the top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tourtieres canadienne(canadian meat pie)
directions: Cut 1/2 cup shortening into salted flour, then add remaining shortening.
Mix well and stir in water.
Roll out 1/2 of dough to line 10-inch pie plate.
Save other 1/2 to top the pie.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Top with slices of uncooked bacon (optional).
Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes, until mixture becomes thick.
Uncover and continue cooking until slightly brown and bacon is crisp.

title: fresh blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Stir to mix well.
Stir in berries.
In small bowl, combine milk, egg and melted oleo.
Beat well and add to dry ingredients all at once.
Mix until moistened. Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chex mix (light)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Molly McButter, together in a large bowl.
Lightly spray with pan spray and toss to cover. Sprinkle with Molly McButter.
Divide evenly into 8 servings and place in Ziploc bags.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook sausage.
Remove half and set aside.
Simmer 1/2 sausage, tomato sauce, paste, water and brown sugar.
In bowl, mix other 1/2 sausage, Ricotta cheese, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese and egg. Cook manicotti according to box directions.
Put 1/3 of sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stuff manicotti with cheese mixture and lay stuffed noodles over sauce.
Put remaining sauce over stuffed noodles.
Put remaining Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Place boned chicken in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Mix in soups and place stuffing on top. Pour broth over.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: eggs and rice
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add rice and stir together.
Put butter in skillet and scramble eggs and rice together.
Salt and pepper and eat!

title: bakers frosting
directions: Cook the flour and milk into a paste. Set aside and cool. In a mixing bowl, cream the oleo, Crisco, sugar and vanilla. Add the cool paste to the creamed mixture. Beat until light and fluffy. Decorate your favorite cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and add chopped pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is firm.
Cool before cutting.

title: (no bake) eclair cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Layer and break crackers for corners and seams.
Divide for top and bottom.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all and bake in muffin pan at 350° until done.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Arrange half
of
apples
in bottom of a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Mix
sugar
and flour and spread half over apples. Pour in rest
of
apples and spread remaining sugar and flour over them. Sprinkle with
cinnamon
and
dot
with butter and dash of nutmeg. Pour
milk
mixed with beaten egg and vanilla over mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Peel, dice and cook potatoes in boiling water; drain.
Combine potatoes with remaining ingredients in casserole.
Stir a couple times.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix milk, mashed potatoes, sugar and lard together.
Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in warm water.
Add to mixture. Next, add 3 cups flour.
Cover and let set 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Then add eggs, salt and remaining flour.
Let rise until double.
Roll, cut and let rise again.
Bake in hot lard.

title: vanilla pudding delight
directions: Mix vanilla, pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer with whole graham crackers.
Spread one-half of the mixture over the crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over mixture.
Spread with the other half of the mixture. Layer again with graham crackers.
Spread with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix the Bisquick and water to form dough.
Place dough in baking dish.
Pat and press dough to make a thin shell in dish, trying to keep shell an even thickness on bottom and up the sides of the baking dish.

title: brittle candy
directions: In cast-iron skillet, mix sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Let boil for 5 minutes until golden brown.
Add nuts and mix well. Pour into platter and let cool.
Break candy into pieces.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food chopper.
Add chopped apples.
Add sugar, nuts and drained pineapple; mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly first 5 ingredients.
Press in an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, building up 1/2-inch edge. Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients for about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake about 25 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pork chops on scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, allowing 1 or 2 large potatoes per person. Slice 1/4-inch thick or less.
Put a layer of potatoes into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and about 1 teaspoon of flour.
Repeat until you reach an inch or so below top edge of casserole.
Place loin pork chops on top; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fill casserole with milk until it shows through the top layer of potatoes, pouring in at one side so it doesn't wash off the seasonings on the meat.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together well.
Shape into ball; chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: angel food strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/3 cup boiling water.
Put strawberry jello with strawberries in jello mold to soak up strawberry mixture. Put
Cool
Whip in middle of cake.	Put in freezer 2 hours before eating.

title: plain cloverleaf dinner rolls
directions: Put yeast in large bowl.
Add 1/4 cup hot water to dissolve yeast.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Knead a few times. Let rise until double in size.
Knead again; let rise again.
The third time, make into rolls.
Put 3 small balls into muffin tins; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: almond crunch
directions: Mix together and bake at 325°, stirring often.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 8 minutes.
Mix 2 sticks butter, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla together and cream for 15 minutes in mixer.
Spread over graham cracker crumbs.
Slice the bananas over sugar mixture.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Then spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Add chopped nuts and cherries to top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: salsa-hot(makes 2 cups)
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, put a layer of refried beans (1 jar), then a layer of salsa, next a layer of shredded Monterey Jack cheese, topped with sour cream and minced tomato to garnish the top.
Can be served hot or cold with nacho chips or in taco shells with lettuce.

title: glazed cherry pie
directions: Mix together and cook until thick and clear; stir constantly. Let cool and pour into a baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Because of the cornstarch this filling does not hold or stand very long.
The pie should be served the day it is made.

title: tropical cheese cake
directions: Mix melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs together. Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs for sprinkling over top.
Press the remaining mixture firmly on bottom and around sides of deep dish pie pan.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mash mush by stirring corn meal and salt into the boiling water; cook 45 minutes.
Brown onion in fat; add meat and stir until it has turned brown.
Add salt and tomatoes.
Grease baking dish; put in layer of mush and meat and cover with mush.
Bake 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.
Cover.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef and drain. Pour into 8x8 deep baking dish. Mix with soup and green beans. Cover with mashed potatoes. Bake at 325° for 30 min., or until mixture bubbles up sides.

title: patty's rice
directions: Brown noodles in butter for 10 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to rapid boil.
Turn off stove; add Minute rice.
Cover and let stand 45 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold with poultry, ham or almost anything.
(Enough to serve South Plattsburgh Fire Department, Auxiliary and whole neighborhood.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix egg with sugar.
Add mashed bananas (better if they are real ripe).
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, more or less.

title: spam salad
directions: Mix together. Add mayonnaise, seasoned with a little sugar, celery and onion salt (if you don't use onion) and 1/2 tsp. mustard.
Serves 12.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Brown onion and margarine.
Add celery.
Add soups, chicken broth, green chilies and pimento.
Cut up chicken and add to mixture.
Tear into pieces the flour tortillas.
Put 1/2 tortillas into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 the sauce mixture over tortillas.
Cover with 1 cup shredded cheese.
Add rest of tortillas and sauce.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly and light brown, about 30 minutes.

title: good morning casserole
directions: Brown sausages and cut into 1/2 inch pieces. Cube bread and place in 9 X 13 pan. Spread sausage pieces and cheese over bread. Add milk to beaten eggs and pour over bread mixture. Spread cream of mushroom soup over top and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll out, cut and bake in hot oven at 350°.
Add nutmeg or grated lemon rind, if preferred.
Will not harden.

title: sugar-free ice cream
directions: Mix pudding and Sweet 'N Low.
Add Pet milk.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in remaining milk.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Can add fruit.

title: one, two, three pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until creamy.
Add milk slowly.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients one cup at a time.
Add vanilla; cream well.
Pour into a greased pan (floured Bundt).
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: savory pork and vegetables
directions: In skillet, melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Cook chops 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Remove chops from skillet. Saute mushrooms with rosemary until tender and liquid has evaporated, stirring often.
Add soup, water and green beans. Heat until boiling.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: In small saucepan over medium flame, heat water and oleo until oleo melts.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Stir in brown sugar and coconut; sprinkle marshmallows and nuts over top.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Cut bacon in half.
Wrap shrimp with bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Marinate in soy sauce about 30 minutes.
Grill until bacon is done.

title: mexican toast
directions: Place in oven at 300° or 350° until cheese is melted.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Brown meat and onions. Drain off excess grease. Add garlic powder, chilies, Lea & Perrins, tomato sauce and cheese. Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese melts. Serve hot in chafing dish. Dip with Fritos, Doritos or similar chips. Serves 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar to eggs.
Add vegetable oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift together the next 5 ingredients and add, a little at a time.
Add a few raisins. After stirring, add nuts.
Bake in two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 4 small loaf pans, greased, for 1 hour at 350°.
When cool, slice and serve with cream cheese.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots into slices.
Cook in small amount of water until barely tender.
Drain and cool.
Slice onion thinly and cut up green pepper.
Combine with carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots, onion and green pepper. Chill.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with 1 cup of flour until flaky.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: caesar salad(serves 8)
directions: Cut garlic into quarters and let sit in 1/2 cup olive oil overnight (out of refrigerator).
Put bread cubes into shallow pan.
Toast them in a slow oven (300°) for 30 minutes until golden brown, turning with a fork.
After cooling, wrap them in wax paper until needed.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix in order given.

title: cereal
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix honey and water.
Stir oil, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt into honey mixture.
Mix both mixtures together.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until brown.

title: holiday appetizer pie
directions: Mix all except pecans and spread in an 8-inch pie plate.
Top with chopped pecans. Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with crackers.

title: easy caramel pie
directions: Simmer unopened can of milk in pan of water for about 2 hours. Be sure the can is covered and is only simmering! Remove from water and let it cool. Open can. Spread into crust. Chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add oil and egg.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts; stir.
Mix soda into flour; mix with butter mixture and add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, or bake into small balls for 12 minutes at 325°.

title: orange pop molded salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
When cool, add pop and chill to whip.
Fold in cream (whipped) and add oranges and marshmallows.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Serve with mixture of 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1/4 cup whipped cream for topping.
Can be served without topping, if desired.

title: strawberry mocha cream tartlets
directions: Combine the flour and salt in a bowl.
Cut in the shortening until uniform but coarse.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of water and toss with a fork, then press into a ball.
Roll out half of the dough at a time on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch circles, then fit inside 2 1/4-inch tart pans and prick with fork.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and remove from tart pans.

title: pecan dessert
directions: Mix flour, pecans, sugar and oleo and press in baking dish. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tamales ole grande
directions: Unwrap tamales and begin to heat in Teflon skillet.
Spoon in between tamales the beans and corn.
(Use no liquids except to rinse the tamale can.)
Heat, stirring gently.

title: krispy kritter
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well blended.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips over hot water (or low heat); spread on top.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: stir-fried turkey and vegetables
directions: In medium bowl, combine sugar, ginger, cornstarch and soy sauce; mix well.
Add turkey or chicken and stir to coat.
Let stand 15 minutes.
In large skillet or wok, heat oil over high heat.
Add carrots and broccoli; stir lightly to coat with oil. Add broth.
Cover; cook 2 minutes.
Add turkey or chicken mixture; stir gently over medium heat.
Add onion; stir-fry about 1 minute. Add mushrooms; stir-fry until mixture is hot.
Serve over rice.

title: company breakfast
directions: Place bread in greased casserole dish. Fry sausage and chop. Beat eggs. Add milk and mix well. Add cut up Velveeta. Sprinkle sausage over bread, then add egg mixture. Cover and chill overnight. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup of hot dog chili sauce. Mix lightly but well.
Press into small loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
To serve, remove from pan; heat remaining hot dog sauce with drippings from meat loaf (approximately 1/4 to 1/2 cup).
Serve with slices of meat loaf.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Mix mustard with small amount of vinegar, then add sugar and salt.
Mix all together with rest of cold vinegar and pour over pickles.
Do not heat.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Rinse and chill potatoes.
Place with onion in buttered casserole.
Heat the margarine over low heat.
Blend flour, salt and milk.
Return to heat and add Cheddar cheese.
Stir.
Bring to boil and add to the potato mixture.
Mix well.
Add pimentos. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until soft but not mushy.
Stir gently. Sauce should be thick and not soupy.
Stirring will prevent soupiness.
Serve 20 minutes after removing from oven.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
In medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and spices.
In small bowl, beat eggs together, milk, sweet potatoes and butter. Add dry ingredients.
Stir until well moistened.
Stir in raisins. Spoon in muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Service warm.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with layer of Keebler crackers. Combine sugars, margarine, graham cracker crumbs and milk in a kettle and bring to a boil.
Stir continuously for 6 to 7 minutes. Pour 1/3 (about 1 cup) of caramel mixture over layer of crackers in pan.
Add a second layer of Keebler crackers and pour 1/3 (1 cup) more of the caramel mixture on top of them.
Add last layer of Keebler crackers and cover with last 1/3 of caramel mixture. Cool in refrigerator 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread over the layered dessert. Cool completely in refrigerator.
Cut in squares.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix mashed bananas with pineapple juice.
Add rest of ingredients.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, mix with 7-Up.

title: southern style minestrone
directions: Combine onion and ground beef in soup pot.
Cook until meat has browned.
Drain excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cover the pan.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
I sometimes add a few drops of Tabasco sauce. I usually do not add salt because most of the canned products already have salt in them.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place beans, corn, onion and pepper in dish first (in layers). Combine soup and sour cream; pour on top.
Place chestnuts and cheese on, then put crackers and butter on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt butter a little and mix with sugar.
Then add 1 egg at a time and beat well.
Now add half of potatoes and then half of milk at a time. Beat well and add rest of potatoes and milk.
Add white Karo and spices. Grease a 3-inch deep dish and sprinkle with very little flour.
Add mixture to pan and sprinkle freely with sugar on top, little hunks of butter and white Karo syrup.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook butter, flour, soup and milk over double boiler.
Combine all ingredients together.
Serve over rice.
Season with pepper, paprika and poultry seasoning.

title: janet's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add boiling water.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Julienne three-quarters of the Swiss cheese.
Set remainder aside.
Dice bacon and cook until crisp. Drain.
Peel and chop onion into large wedges.

title: dinosaur food(for the kids)
directions: Mix dirt and swamp water.
Add crushed bones and fat.
Heat and bring to a boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and stir in grass and squashed bugs.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool until firm.

title: fudge cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour, butter and sugar; beat to resemble crumbs.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine frosting and cheese.
Add eggs; beat smooth. Spread over crust.
Sprinkle nuts.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes. Cool; cut.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 32.

title: italian minestrone with tortellini
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, brown sausage and drain.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add beef broth, red wine, tomatoes, carrots, celery, ketchup, Italian seasoning and garlic.
Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add zucchini, tortellini, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer, covered, until tortellini are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: ranchero baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef and drain grease. Add all ingredients together and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Cover berries with water and boil until soft.
Strain and return to pan.
Add butter and sugar.
Boil until sugar melts. Drop pieces of dough into berry juice.
After dumplings are done pour into baking dish and top with strips of dough. Spread melted butter on dough and sprinkle with sugar. Bake in 400 degree oven until brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend sugar, peaches, flavor and melted margarine together. Add 1 pie crust to top.
Bake 30 minutes, then remove.
Let sit until cool.

title: peach crisp
directions: In 8 or 9-inch pan, spread peaches covered with 1/2 cup peach juice.
Combine all other ingredients and toss with fork and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is lightly browned.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or cold.
Serves 6.

title: mozzarella tamale
directions: In skillet, brown ground chuck. Add chopped onion and green pepper; saute.
Add chili seasoning mix and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in shredded cheeses and olives. Turn into 9-inch square dish.
Prepare the corn bread mix according to directions. Arrange spoonfuls on top.
(Extra can be made into muffins.)
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: new orleans shrimp creole
directions: Saute in oleo first five ingredients.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add 1 pound deveined shrimp and 1 pound crab meat.
Cook slowly 30 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.
(Makes 6 to 8 servings.)

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; form together edges on large pizza pan. Bake per package directions for about 12 minutes; cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise; beat until smooth.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Place raw broccoli and cauliflower on top of cream cheese mixture; press down gently with hands.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Additional raw vegetables may be added or substituted for broccoli and cauliflower.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients except milk and chives in saucepan and simmer covered, until potatoes are tender; about 15 minutes.
Add milk.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Garnish with chives.
Makes 5 cups.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix together graham cracker crumbs, a small amount of melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put crust in cupcake papers.
Let set in refrigerator 20 minutes.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix yolks and other ingredients together.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sam's easy bake apple pie
directions: Mix apples and spices.
Spread in greased pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat next 5 ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour over apples. Sprinkle with streusel.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.

title: early spanish rice
directions: Cook the first five ingredients until vegetables are tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, over low heat, until rice is done, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamed turkey
directions: Melt shortening; stir in flour.
Add milk and cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in turkey, vegetable, salt and pepper and heat thoroughly.
Serve over biscuit or rice.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 23 g, protein 25 g, fat 15 g, calories 327.
One serving = 3 meat low-fat exchange, 1 fat exchange, 1 vegetable exchange.
Add a bread starch exchange for biscuit or rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix pudding and corn syrup together.
Add milk and egg.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until top cracks and is golden brown.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and combine.
Mix vinegar and sugar together and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Will keep 2 weeks if covered tightly.

title: aunt yvonne's baked beans with sausage
directions: Fry sausage until crumbled and done, but not brown.
In a large bowl, combine sausage, onion, pork and beans and sugar. Dissolve ginger, salt and dry mustard in hot water.
Stir into bean mixture.
Pour into large 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green and red peppers, onions, cream cheese and 1/2 cup salsa in saucepan on low heat until cheese is melted. Spoon 1/3 cup steak, chicken or turkey

mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up. Place seam side down in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch pan. Stir cheese and milk in saucepan on low heat until smooth. Pour sauce over tortillas. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick and easy chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool cake and poke holes in it with a drinking straw.
Mix pudding and milk and pour in holes and over cake.
Spread frosting over cake.
Melt chocolate chips and Crisco in microwave and drizzle over frosting.
Best if put in refrigerator overnight.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Mix in flour, then French onion soup and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on bread.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Heat Sugar until melted and golden brown.
Add Hot Water carefully.
Add Brown Sugar and cook until mixture is like a soft ball.
Pour over Popped Corn and roll into balls.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add corn, salt, sugar, pepper, flour and melted butter; mix. Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into a greased baking dish and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hors d'oeuvre pie
directions: On a large baking sheet, pat pastry into 11 inch circle. Pierce thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 425° oven 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: toasted pecan cheese log
directions: Spread pecans in a single layer in a 9-inch square baking dish. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 5 to 6 minutes or until toasted. Set aside.
Combine green pepper, onion and butter in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Microwave at High for 45 seconds or until veggies are crisp-tender, stirring once.
Drain and set aside.

title: zesty rice salad
directions: Boil chicken broth.
Add rice.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients together.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Beat the egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
By tablespoonfuls, gradually add sugar, beating very stiff.
Fold in coconut and orange or lemon rind.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet, lined with aluminum foil (ungreased).
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 20 minutes or delicately browned.
Store kisses in an airtight container.

title: shrimp wiggle
directions: Combine onion and tomato soup.
Cook rice; add to onion and soup.
Add the juice from 1 can of shrimp, canned milk and 2 cans of shrimp.
Heat through and serve.
(Can also substitute shrimp with tuna, chicken, etc.)

title: mom's gravy
directions: Cook together the fat and flour, then add water (preferably warm) and seasoning to taste.

title: one dish meal
directions: Grease 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Crumble ground beef for first layer. Slice onion on this. Next, add sliced potatoes, then put a layer of drained corn. On top, spread soup as it comes from the can. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: butterscotch better 'n better
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoons onto buttered cookie sheet (1/2 teaspoon
dough for each cookie).
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Allow
to "set" for a minute on cookie sheet before removing.

title: spinach-cheese chicken rolls
directions: Dip cutlets in egg and then bread crumbs; set aside.
Cook spinach or microwave and drain well.
Add oil, garlic and 8 ounces of the Mozzarella cheese.
Grease bottom of oblong dish with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Place approximately 2 tablespoons of spinach mixture at thin end of cutlet.
Roll and place seam side down.
Drizzle remaining butter over stuffed, rolled cutlets in dish.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove pan from oven.
Place remaining Mozzarella on cutlets.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix the milk, pudding and vanilla. Combine all and fold in Cool Whip. Crush Oreos.
Put half in bottom.
Put in mixture and other half of Oreos on top.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients until mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Press rolls into greased pizza pan.
Seal

title: bean dip(heart smart)
directions: In blender or food processor at medium speed, puree all ingredients until smooth; place in small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature about 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings, about 2 tablespoons each.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt marshmallows together with milk, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Chill until thickened.
Blend in liqueurs.
Whip the cream until stiff; fold in marshmallow mixture and food coloring. Pour into crust.
Chill for at least 5 hours.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour
peaches
into
baking
dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk, melted margarine and cornstarch;
mix thoroughly. Pour slowly around top of peaches.
Bake at 400° for almost 1 hour
or until golden brown.
Juice will thicken when cobbler begins to cool.
Recipe can be doubled for get-togethers.
Top with favorite ice cream.

title: pepperidge farm patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Brown in a small amount of oil on medium heat.
Makes about 8 to 10 patties.
Can be warmed in oven after browned and served with mushroom or golden mushroom soup poured over them.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Combine the softened cream cheese with 1 cup of milk until well blended.
Add pudding and other cup of milk; mix until pudding begins to thicken.
Pour into pie crust and chill. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: carrot and oat bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and raisins together.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites; add milk, honey, oil and carrots.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; mix only until moistened.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pans.
Can be frozen.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Soak crumbs with milk until moist.
Add 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Add ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Knife inserted must come out clean.
May be doubled.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add peanut butter, then add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla. Sift soda and flour together.
Add to the mixture.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and salt.
Stir in the flour.
Put into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: boil cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Let boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper to cool.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown hamburg; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; add water. Cook about 1 hour, then add rice last and chili beans.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: beef garden casserole
directions: Cook onion in small amount of fat until tender, not brown.
Add ground beef and seasonings; brown lightly.
Add green beans, corn and tomato soup and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in 400° oven until done.
Always cook in muffin pan.

title: cheesy beef-stuffed peppers
directions: Place peppers in 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) glass baking dish; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except shredded cheese, in medium bowl; mix well.
Spoon meat mixture into green pepper halves.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave for 24 to 26 minutes on Roast, or until meat is well done (about 140°).
Top with shredded cheese and continue cooking on Roast until cheese is melted. Makes about 6 servings.

title: lime salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add
lime Jell-O and cream cheese.
Mix thoroughly, then add ice
cream
and nuts.	Put red maraschino cherries on top for garnish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, water and 1/4 cup butter in bowl; mix well. Layer chicken, stuffing mix and soup mixture, 1/2 at a time in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: double crunchy chip cookies
directions: Stir flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Set aside. In large mixing bowl beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add 2 cups crushed Kellogg's flakes and chocolate and butterscotch morsels.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls into remaining crushed cereal, coating dough completely.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until creamy.
Blend in remaining ingredients except walnuts and paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts and sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix and bake in flat pan or layers at 350° until done.
Heat 1 cup milk and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cook 5 minutes and add 1 cup coconut. Pour on cake.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt all together and then let cool.
After cooled, mix in 1 large container of Cool Whip and place in a baked pie shell and chill.
Serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until firm.

title: lime torte
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy. Add flour and mix well. Press this onto bottom and halfway up sides of bottom. Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes until lightly browned. Cool.
Reserve 2 tablespoons nuts for topping. Sprinkle remaining nuts on bottom of baked crust.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend sour cream with remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled. Especially good with saltine crackers. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter, vinegar, vanilla and salt. Beat well.
Stir
in
coconut. Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: cobbler crust
directions: Combine all ingredient.
Pour into bottom of a baking dish. Pour cooked fruit over the batter.
Bake at 350 or 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain and chill corn.
In a large bowl, mix corn, red onion, green pepper and parsley.
In a small bowl whisk together sour cream and broth.
Add vinegar; whisk to blend.
Whisk in mayonnaise; beat until light and frothy.
Toss cream mixture, salt and pepper with vegetable mixture.
Chill.
When ready to serve, garnish with tomato, bacon and green onion.
Serves 8.

title: gumbo
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Saute peppers, onions, celery and garlic.
Add tomato sauce with chopped tomatoes and fresh, diced tomatoes.
Add water and simmer.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with chopped onions and pepper. Drain off grease and add ketchup to mixture and cook for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: salsa roja
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley, basil and chives in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, lower the heat and cover.
Simmer for 40 to 50 minutes.
Add minced herbs to taste.

title: sue's spicy baked chicken
directions: In food processor, puree spinach, Feta, butter and jalapeno until it is a paste.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soup, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour evenly over mixture in dish.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: stir-fry spaghetti with beef
directions: In medium bowl combine soy, garlic, ginger and beef.
Toss to coat well.
Marinate 1/2 to 1 hour.
In medium skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add beef mixture and broccoli, stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add onion, peppers and mushrooms.
Stir until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Blend water, cornstarch, bouillon and salt. Stir in beef mixture.
Cook until thickened and translucent.
Mix stir-fry mixture with pasta noodles.
Serve hot.
Enjoy.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Cool, peel and mash. Add remaining ingredients.
Put into baking dish. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Top with marshmallows and brown.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Wash and drain chicken and turkey parts.
Remove head and shells from shrimp.
Put in cold water for later.
Boil chicken gizzards in the gumbo pot.
Add onion, celery, garlic, Season-All, salt and pepper.
Cook until the onion is clear.
While the gizzards are boiling, slightly brown all meats.
Place the meats aside for later.
Now make a roux by browning flour in cooking oil in another skillet.
Do not overbrown roux.
If it is too dark, discard and make again, stopping when it is a golden brown.

title: stuffed italian shells
directions: Mix all ingredients except shells and sauce.
Stuff mixture into shells.
Coat bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with a little sauce.
Put stuffed shells in the pan, open side up.
Pour sauce over the shells.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy cucumber pickles
directions: Peel, cut out seed and cut cucumbers into lengthwise strips. Soak 24 hours in 2 gallons of water with 2 cups of lime added.

title: eggplant stew
directions: Early in day, peel and slice eggplant; then place slices on plate, salt and leave for several hours until bitter juice comes out.
In stew pot, fry stew meat and onions until meat is brown. Add 3 cups water, salt, pepper, turmeric, garlic and lemon to meat. Boil 5 minutes, then add tomato sauce.
Cook on medium heat (an even simmer) for about 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add yellow peas and simmer 30 minutes more until peas are soft (not mushy).
While stew meat is simmering, wash eggplant and dry off. Fry eggplant seasoned with turmeric in skillet until golden brown. Drain off excess oil with paper towels.
When peas are done, add eggplant to meat.
Serve with rice.

title: bo jangle biscuits
directions: Mix and bake as any other biscuit.

title: grilled baby back ribs
directions: Strip the membrane from each rib slab by running a paring knife under a corner of the membrane, grasping it with a dry paper towel and pulling it off in a single motion to the end of the rib slab.
Salt each slab sparingly on both sides with "Charlie's" 30 minutes before grilling.
After grilling, separate ribs by cutting through the meaty portion between each bone.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off grease and mix together tomato soup, green beans and ground beef.
Pour into a baking dish; mix plain flour and buttermilk together.
Make a dough mixture.
Put on top of soup, green beans and ground beef.
Pour dough mixture. Bake at 350° to 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is brown. Serve.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Mix ingredients; pour over bacon.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over endive, escarole, dandelion or lettuce.

title: basic turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Combine all ingredients;
place in lightly
greased
x
8 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan or shape in loaf form and place in 1 quart lightly greased baking dish. Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: easy omelet
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet on medium heat.
Add eggs. Lift edges of eggs as they cook.
Let uncooked portions run under cooked part.
Cook until set.
Put filling on 1/2 of omelet and fold over.
Makes 2 servings.

title: banana loaf
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and bananas.
Beat well. Add Bisquick and nuts; stir until well blended.
Pour into well greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack before slicing.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Do not open oven until cake has baked at least one hour or it will fall!!!

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and parsley. Cut up the lettuce, celery and onions.
Heat 2 tablespoons sugar with the almonds until crystalized.
Mix all ingredients only when ready to serve.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Prebake pie shell at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fry (or bake) bacon until crisp; crumble into small pieces to yield 3/4 cup. Combine eggs, milk, nutmeg, onion, salt and pepper.
Beat well. Sprinkle prebaked pie shell with cheese and bacon; pour in egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate. Serves about 10.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crush cookies with rolling pin (reserve a few crumbs to sprinkle on top of pie) and mix with melted butter.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate and chill in freezer.
Place marshmallows and milk into double boiler.
Heat until melted.
Remove and cool. Add creme de cacao and creme de menthe.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour mixture over crust and freeze overnight.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over pie.
Cover with foil and keep frozen until time to use.
Remove from refrigerator 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain frozen vegetables.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes.
Chop onions and bell peppers.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Cook until mixture thickens like catsup.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream or ice cream if wanted.
Served plain is real good.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes raw.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Drop by tablespoons and fry to a golden brown in butter or other shortening.

title: pot roasted doves
directions: Brown onions, white bottoms of green onions and bell pepper in butter.
At the same time boil dove breasts for 15 minutes; drain and season with Worcestershire sauce and Season-All.
When onions are golden brown, add doves, garlic and 1/2 green onion tops. Cook 10 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Add 1 cup water. Cover and cook on low fire for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently. Doves will cook in onion juice and water.
Add rest of onion tops and 1 more cup of water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve with pot of white beans and rice and French bread.

title: old-fashioned apple dumplings
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg; add butter. Pare apples and remove core with peach pitter, leaving apple whole. Sift flour, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening. Add milk all at once and stir until moistened. Roll 1/4 inch thick and in 5-inch squares. Place apple on square of dough; fill center with cinnamon candies. Dot with butter, fold corners to center, pinch edges together and seal. Place an inch apart in greased baking pan. Pour over syrup. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: krupnik(barley soup)
directions: Cube leftover bread and place the cubes on a paper towel in your microwave.
Microwave on High power until they are hard, about 1 minute. Combine dried herbs and spices of your choice. For example, basil, thyme, parsley, paprika and pepper.
Place in paper or plastic bag with the hardened cubes. Shake well.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast as directed.
Combine with sugar, set aside. Sift together dry ingredients.
Work in shortening.
Add liquid mixture (yeast mixed with water and sugar).
Add extra flour as needed to make workable.
Roll out/ cut with biscuit cutter. Place on baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine rest of ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well; add to zucchini mixture.
Pour in a 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap water chestnuts in bacon (hold with toothpicks). Mix Teriyaki sauce and a little minced garlic. Pour over chestnuts. Marinade for 1- 1 1/2 hours (don't over marinade). Drain. Cook at 400° until bacon is done.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut up chicken and place in baking dish.
Heat broth and soup until smooth.
Place aside.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour broth over cut up chicken.
Pour flour mixture over it all.
Bake 30 minutes at 425° until crust is brown.

title: grandma flanders' sweet dough
directions: Soften yeast in about 1 cup warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar. Add butter, sugar and salt to 1 cup scalded milk.
Use the other cup of milk to slowly cool the scalded milk to lukewarm, stirring continuously.
Add yeast, eggs and flour to make stiff batter. Add remaining flour and knead.
Let rise to double the bulk. Roll out to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with round
cookie cutter; fold in half and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ruby broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour into casserole dish, top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes approximately 48 (4 ounce) servings.
Excellent source of vitamin C.

title: sweet and sour sauteed cabbage
directions: Coarsely shred cabbage; set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add apples; cook them, stirring, for about 3 to 5 minutes, until they begin to soften.
Mix in the lemon juice, brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves.
Add cabbage; stir-fry until the cabbage is tender but still crunchy, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve right away.

title: shrimp tomato salad
directions: Heat soup and add gelatin.
Whip cream cheese and add mayonnaise; blend into soup.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and shrimp.
Pour into oiled mold and let chill until firm.

title: turkey crunch
directions: Mix
together
first
six
ingredients	and
pour
into greased casserole dish.
Blend soup and milk together and pour over all. Sprinkle	noodles
on top and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water in large covered freezer container.
Cool.
Add orange juice concentrate, water, lemon juice, pineapple juice and bananas; mix well.
Freeze.
Thaw for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Ladle into cups.

title: apple cake
directions: Place flour, sugar, soda, salt and spices in mixing bowl.
Add oil and blend well.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, cubed apples and nuts; stir.
Place in cold oven and turn heat to 275° for 10 minutes.
Then turn to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let cool before turning out.

title: buttery grated carrots
directions: Place carrots in skillet with tight-fitting lid, add water, salad oil, garlic salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Cover skillet and cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle butter substitute over mixture; blend and serve.

title: buttery fish 'n stuffing
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt 1/3 cup margarine; add sesame seed, parsley, celery salt and wine.
Toss with stuffing mix.
Place fish in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon stuffing mix over fillets. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into balls.
Place in muffin tin and spread balls to form crusts.

title: blueberry salad (congealed)
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and let congeal.
Mix next 4 ingredients well and spread over congealed salad.
This makes a large oblong Pyrex dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix as directed on box, then add Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Make a layer of sliced bananas and vanilla wafers, then add pudding mixture.
Repeat layers and top with wafers.

title: dumplings
directions: Roll to about 1/4-inch thick and cut in squares and drop in chicken broth.
(I double the recipe.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Braise onion.
Beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese.
Mix all together and bake 20 to 35 minutes at 400° in hot skillet.

title: top of stove candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Peel and cut lengthwise.
Set aside.
Simmer in a pan the next 5 ingredients until the sugar dissolves.
Add the potato halves and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Cook until potatoes are glazed and the syrup thickened.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Turn into a serving dish.

title: steak parmigiana
directions: Combine flour
and
cheese,
then in separate bowl, dip steak in egg
and
coat with flour mixture.
Brown in hot oil. Place in shallow
baking
dish.
Saute
onion in oil and then stir in tomato paste,
garlic, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Pour sauce
over
steak
and
top with Mozzarella cheese slices. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.	Serve over noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter poke cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for 13 x 9-inch cake.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes at once down through cake to pan with plastic drinking straw, using turning motion to make large holes.
Holes should be at 1-inch intervals.

title: carol's forgotten cookies
directions: Beat the egg whites until frothy.
Add the sugar gradually. Beat until stiff peaks form. Fold in the pecans and chocolate chips. Add the vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350° and turn oven off.
Place cookies in oven and leave in oven overnight or until cookies are cool.

title: chocolate town syrup cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add flour mixture alternately with chocolate syrup and vanilla to creamed mixture. Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef; add next 6 ingredients.
Cook until onion is done. Mix soft cream cheese and sour cream with cooked noodles.
Put in 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Put meat mixture on top and cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° until bubbly hot, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli egg and cheese casserole
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine and toss in bread cubes, stirring until coated well.
Brown lightly. Continue to stir until evenly brown.
Set aside.
In bowl, beat eggs, milk, flour and mustard together until well mixed.
Add cheese, broccoli and ham.
Place bread in a greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour or until eggs are set.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: fried green onions
directions: Slice onions.
Put in bowl.
Put self-rising flour in another bowl with pinch of salt.
Dip onions in mixture of first 6 ingredients, then dip in flour.
Fry in hot Crisco.
Let brown on each side.

title: cucumber-stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off each tomato; scoop out pulp.
Invert tomatoes on paper towels and let stand 30 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, shredded cucumber, curry powder and garlic salt.
Beat until well blended.
Spoon mixture into tomato shells.
Garnish each tomato with a cucumber wedge by placing pointed end into mixture.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs, oil and salt together; add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
If you add too much flour, add a little warm water until it is the right consistency.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Roll out as thin as possible on a floured board or countertop.
Cut into strips of desired width with a sharp knife.
Cut a little smaller than you wish the finished product to be since they will swell a little as they cook.
Use in soup or cook in boiling water, salted and use as desired.

title: warren's fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in bread tins for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: mexican angel breaths
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff and dry.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on pressed cookie sheet.
Put in oven. Leave in overnight or for over 2 hours.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Coat chicken with butter and mayonnaise.
Roll in mixture of crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place in a baking dish.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: light corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in oil over medium-high heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, broth and Creole seasoning.
Boil. Add noodles and lower heat to medium; simmer for 8 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and parsley.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: ham and cheese dip
directions: In a medium bowl, blend all ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with additional chopped pimento.
Serve with crackers, chips, vegetables or as sandwich spread.

title: colorful chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Store in refrigerator.

title: four layer delight
directions: First Layer:
Cream butter or margarine, flour and nuts. Press into long Pyrex dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Spread apples evenly over bottom. Mix ingredients until crumb-like.
Sprinkle over apples.
Pour 1/3 cup melted butter over mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexicalli rice
directions: In large skillet, cook beef until lightly browned; add onion and peppers and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally until rice is done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: evelyn's fruit cookies(better than fruit cake!)
directions: Option:
Cut down on the raisins and currants and use chopped dried peaches, apples, prunes and even dried cherries.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until half done, add chopped onions, fry until tender.
Add 2/3 cup flour, stir until smooth.
Add milk and stir until thick and low boil.
Add potatoes.

title: easy salad(diet)
directions: Dump all ingredients together and beat with an electric mixer until well blended.

title: louise-e-anna yummey
directions: Mix; pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Pour coconut and nuts in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Make sure to grease pan with oleo.
Make German chocolate cake mix according to box and pour over nuts and coconut.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all together except chocolate chips.
Stir those in last. Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Crumble beef in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook in microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.

title: mexican frito salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, onions and beans.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Grate cheese and crush Fritos.
Add cheese, Fritos and dressing right before serving.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix soda in buttermilk;
let
stand
for a few minutes. Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening; add egg yolks, one at a
time,
beating
well after each addition;	 add buttermilk	alternately
with
flour
to
creamed mixture.	Stir in vanilla.
Fold
in
whites
gently.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Bake in 3 layers for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Wash pieces of chicken breast.
Place in baking pan and spread oil over.
Sprinkle lemon juice or black pepper with lemon over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix butter, Old English spread, mayonnaise, onion and garlic salt with mixer.
Fold in crab meat.
Open English muffins and spread about 2 tablespoons on top of muffin.
Cut into quarters. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: cinnamon sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan, combine the brown sugar, corn syrup and butter; cook and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add the pecans.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
In a shallow bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit in half; dip in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place, cut side down, over brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert onto a serving plate; serve warm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: barbecue pork roast
directions: Cook a Boston butt or pork picnic in an open pan for 12 hours at 225°.
Cool and shred meat.

title: cheese quiche
directions: Pie shell should have high fluted edge.
Sprinkle bacon into pie shell.
Combine Cheddar cheese soup and egg yolks.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in Tabasco sauce.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Serve warm.
Cut into wedges. Garnish with bacon curls and chopped chives.

title: frozen strawberry meringue
directions: Rinse and crush berries in small bowl.
Set aside 1 cup for meringue.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar and beat until it peaks.
Mix the 1 cup berries and the meringue.
Sweeten remaining berries with powdered sugar.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mock italian meat balls ii
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fry in corn oil slowly until brown. Make round patties about the size of an egg.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding by directions on box; then add Cool Whip.
Put a layer of crackers in dish; then spread pudding over this.
Make 2 layers and then place crackers over the top layer.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: broccoli mushroom saute
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into portions.
Set aside.
Bring the saucepan full of water to a boil and add the salt and baking soda. Immerse the broccoli and poach for 5 minutes.
Remove and drain. Heat the butter in the skillet and saute the garlic and sliced mushrooms until tender.
Add the broccoli and toss until well coated with butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans on bottom of pie shell.
(Poke the pie shell with a fork.)
Blend other ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until middle of the pie does not shake.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cover broccoli with water and cook until tender.
(Mash a little bit.)
Add margarine or butter, chicken bouillon and evaporated milk.
Thicken with cornstarch until desired thickness.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix sugar and coffee granules with hot water and sprinkle over crumbled brownies.
In large compote dish or bowl, layer part of brownies, pudding mix, whipped topping and crushed candy.
Repeat layers, ending with whipped topping and candy.
Chill until serving time.

title: english pie
directions: Cream together sugar and egg
yolks.
Add
vanilla
and oleo. Mix well.
