Roll raisins and pecans in flour.
Stir into first mixture.
Pour in well beaten
egg
whites
last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bow tie pasta with fresh broccoli
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Saute onion and garlic in oil over low heat until soft.
Add broccoli.
Cook a minute over medium heat.
Add wine and stock; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until liquid is reduced by 1/3.
Add grated cheese and basil and toss over warm pasta.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in crock-pot.
Separate breasts from bone. Put chicken in crock-pot.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken. Cook on high for 2 hours or until rice is tender.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Put frozen fish, sugar, vinegar and salt in cold water.
Bring to boil.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Put in broiler for a few minutes with butter and paprika.
Dip in hot butter.
Enjoy!

title: pralines
directions: Cook over medium heat until soft ball stage. Stir constantly. Cook in large pan.
It will foam up.
When cooked add vanilla, butter and pecans. Beat well until thick.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Slice off tops of rolls; set aside.
Mix together mustard, margarine, poppy seed and onion.
Spread evenly over top and bottom of rolls.
Evenly distribute ham over bottom of rolls, then sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tops are brown.
Cut into individual rolls.

title: best easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 8 x 10 baking dish. Spread fruit evenly in dish. Mix flour, sugar, milk and vanilla 2 minutes. Stir in chipped butter. Pour mixture over fruit. Bake until top is golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla.
Stir in the zucchini. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir into the first mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook white sugar, butter and evaporated milk to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
When done, remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until thick.
Pour into greased dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix and micro the sugar and lite syrup on High for 5 minutes. Stir in the peanuts; micro on High 4 minutes.
Add the butter and vanilla; stir and micro on High 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave. Add the baking soda; spread immediately on greased cookie sheet. Cool for 1 hour; break into pieces.
A 4-cup glass measuring cup works well.

title: baked beans
directions: Put onion, green pepper, brown sugar, catsup and mustard in bacon grease; simmer until clear.
Pour in the pork and beans; let simmer for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon on top; simmer a few minutes more.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese in a double boiler.
Add crabmeat and onion.
Continue.
Serve with toast points or crackers.

title: linda's chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam.
Cut chicken breasts into serving pieces.
Place chicken in the bottom of the baking dish.
Layer cheese over chicken.
In a bowl, combine soup and water.
Mix until creamy.
Pour the mixture over chicken and cheese in the baking dish.
In another bowl, combine stuffing mix and butter.
Mix well.
Spoon over the soup, covering the entire top of the casserole.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until chicken is tender and topping is browned.
Serves 5.

title: mazidra
directions: Butter souffle dish.
Put eggs, cream, Parmesan, mustard, salt and pepper in blender or food processor.
Whirl until smooth.
Cut Cheddar and cream cheese into pieces and add.
Whirl until smooth and thick.
Pour into dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes for soft, liquidy center (delicious sauce to spoon over) or 50 minutes for a firm souffle.
I prefer the soft liquidy center.

title: granny's fruit salad
directions: Chill fruit cocktail; drain.
Add chopped, fresh fruit, nuts and miniature marshmallows.

title: better than almost anything cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Generously grease bottom of 9 x 13 pan with shortening. Make cake mix as directed on package using water, oil & eggs. Pour into pan, bake 30-35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix and brown in hot oil.

title: campfire corndogs
directions: Wrap hot dogs with cornbread by stretching down and around. Bake on a stick over the fire.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef; drain. Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion. Line muffin cups with biscuit dough, pressing dough up to edge of cups. Spoon meat into cups. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into ball and roll in parsley flakes.

title: shrimp dip(easy and everyone raves!!)
directions: Drain shrimp; mash with a fork.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Make 3 days ahead so that flavors may blend.
Serve with Triscuits, chips or your favorite crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: creole eye of round roast
directions: You will also need 1 large size (14 x 20-inches) oven bag.

title: special occasion chicken and dressing
directions: Boil hen slowly until tender.
Set aside to cool.
Sift together flour, meal, salt and soda.
Add chopped onion, milk and eggs.
Mix well and add sage and black pepper.
Pour in generously greased pan and bake at 450° until brown.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Combine sugars, salt and milk in heavy saucepan.
Stir over low heat until mixture begins to boil.
Cook to 236° or soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Cool to lukewarm, 110° without stirring.
Add vanilla; beat until it loses its gloss.
Pour into pan.
Cut after cooling.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil and boil constantly (while stirring) for 10 minutes.
Have oleo and chocolate chips in bowl. Add sugar and milk mixture to chips and oleo and beat quickly; beat, beat, beat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into large 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Makes 5 pounds.
Do not refrigerate.

title: cobbler dough
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into bottom of baking dish and pour in fruit.
Crust will rise to the top.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix liquids, then add dry ingredients.
May add 3 mashed bananas and 1/2 cup chopped pecans for great banana nut bread. Cook 1 hour in Bundt cake pan at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix together soups, sour cream, milk, pepper and onion. Add cooked chicken and spaghetti to above ingredients. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Layer top with cheese slices. Crush and mix crackers with butter and layer on top of cheese slices. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine; mix.
Put half of this mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
In saucepan, combine zucchini, onions and salted water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and spread over stuffing mix.
Combine sour cream, soup and carrots; mix.
Spread over zucchini and top with remainder of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except nuts, at low speed until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch (or layer pan).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Spread on frosting when cool.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Combine
the
tomato
juice,
tomatoes, cream of tomato soup, 1/2
gallon
water, salt, sugar and pepper.
Bring to a boil and let cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add the rice and stir to
keep from sticking on the bottom of the pot.
Cook over a low
fire until the rice becomes very done; stir at intervals. The rice should serve
as
a
roux (cooking oil and flour mixture) to tighten the soup.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put layer of dried beef in bottom of dish.
Place chicken on beef.
Mix soup, sour cream and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet with a little olive oil.
Add onion, garlic, oregano, bay leaves and Ragu.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix cheese, sour cream and onions.
Set aside.
Cook noodles as directed.
Add a little olive oil to water.
Drain. Spread 3/4 of noodles into a large rectangular pan.
Pour meat sauce over noodles.
Spread the cheese, sour cream and onions over sauce.
Put remainder of noodles over all.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour, pecans and vanilla. Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: zippy crisp chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with salad dressing; coat with combined crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake one (1) hour or until tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: green peas delicious
directions: Celery and water chestnuts are optional.

title: apple butternut squash soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add the diced onion and cook until translucent.
Add the broth, squash, potatoes, apple, salt and pepper.
Increase the heat to medium-high and bring the broth to a boil.
Reduce the heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until the squash and potatoes are tender.
With a slotted spoon, remove the squash, potatoes and apples and place in a food processor or blender.
Pure ingredients. Return the pure to the broth in the saucepan and stir to combine.
Add applesauce, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir until well blended. Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings. Prep time: about 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; toss lightly.
Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serve at once.
This can be prepared in advance and stored in refrigerator until time to add topping and bake.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate chips and syrup together over slow heat, stirring constantly.
Cool partially.
Add one small can of evaporated milk; stir until well blended.
Serve over ice cream. (Keeps very well.)

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Drain and set aside; add beans, barbecue sauce, ketchup, sugar, brown sugar, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or in a crock-pot on low heat for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone 1 chicken; set aside.
Save chicken broth for later use in recipe.
Put 1 bag of Doritos in bottom of large casserole dish.
Dice 1 onion and 1 bell pepper and put on top of Doritos.
Put chicken on top of this.
Pour 1 can of cream of chicken soup on top.
Pour 1 can of golden mushroom soup on top. Pour 1 1/2 cups chicken broth on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze according to directions of freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: easy great dessert
directions: Can also use coconut with green cherries.

title: russian scalloped potatoes
directions: Simmer the onions in half the butter until soft, but not brown.
Add the flour; cook 5 minutes, then add consomme, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Continue cooking 10 minutes over low heat.
Slice potatoes thin and saute in remaining butter about 5 minutes.

title: summer squash
directions: Cover mixture with water.
Cover and cook on low heat until veggies are soft.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; set aside to dry.
Slice onion thin; saute in bacon grease.
Mix ketchup and brown sugar in bowl, then pour onion and bacon grease into this mixture and mix thoroughly. Pour over beans in baking dish; mix slightly.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top of beans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: andrea's chocolate cream filled cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Beat in oil, sour milk and egg; beat for 3 minutes.
Add hot water and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 25 minutes.

title: turkey wings over rice
directions: Put cleaned turkey wings in crock-pot.
Pour soup and/or gravy over top of turkey wings.
Add water.
Cover crock-pot and cook on low or automatic setting until tender, about 7 hours.
Remove skin from turkey wings.
They usually fall apart because they're very tender.
Pick meat off bones and set aside.
Spoon fat off broth. Pour broth in small pan.
Mix cornstarch and water in a glass. Pour into broth and heat until thickened to desired consistency. Put meat in gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: taco party wings
directions: Combine taco seasoning, cornmeal, salt and parsley flakes in a plastic bag.
Shake wings in bag, a few at a time, until coated. Place in single layer on greased shallow baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Turn wings and bake 10 minutes or until tender.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, deviled ham, scallions and chilies; mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Makes 1 (2-cup) cheese ball.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Divide the mashed potatoes into 8 equal parts.
Use your hands and form 1/2-inch thick patties.

title: strawberry yum-yum
directions: Mix stick of butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Press in oblong dish.
Combine eggs, 1 cup butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Spread strawberry pie filling next, then top with Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours.

title: date nut dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar and warm water in saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour in 8 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pan. With fork, blend butter and brown sugar; add milk, flour and baking powder.
Blend thoroughly; add dates and nuts.
Mix to form soft, slightly sticky dough.
Do not roll and do not stir once it is mixed.
Remove from bowl and drop into pan atop brown sugar syrup.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce in large bowl.
Place in a large 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Shape into a loaf.

title: "egg"-citing cheese flan
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Pour honey in pan.
In a bowl, beat condensed milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture into the pan.

title: crab dip
directions: Place the block of cream cheese on a large plate or tray.
In a medium-size bowl, combine the crab meat and 3/4 of the cocktail sauce.
Pour over the block of cream cheese.
Use the remaining cocktail sauce for extra taste.

title: one pot brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; stir constantly until smooth.
Stir in sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla, then flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: new zealand salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and beat until smooth.
Store in a salad container in refrigerator.
Quick and easy.

title: mom's vinegar taffy
directions: Combine ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat without stirring until it reaches hard ball stage.
Pour out onto buttered platter.
Let cool just long enough, until you can hold it in your hands.
Pull as long as possible (should be white when finished).
Twist into a long rope; let cool on wax paper.

title: vegetable soup
directions: * Can substitute 1 large can V-8 juice.

title: magic lemon pie
directions: Make a graham cracker or vanilla wafer crust.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and egg yolks together.
Add lemon juice last.
Lemon juice "cooks" eggs.
The filling will become thick.
Pour into crust and beat egg whites until fluffy and pour over pie.
Brown in oven. It slices better if you chill it before serving.

title: amaretto punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Let cool.
Poke holes in top of cake with a fork all over.
Pour the Amaretto on top of cake evenly. Cut cake into cubes.
Put half the cake into a punch bowl.
Put half the chopped toffee bars on top of the cake in the punch bowl. Spread half a container of Cool Whip on top of cake and toffee bars. Repeat the process.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend butter or margarine with the stuffing.
Line baking dish (10 x 10-inch) with 1/2 of crumbs.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour in dish and top with rest of the crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad supreme
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator at least 4 hours.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions and drain.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Add cheese and soup. Cook all over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Do not boil.
Serve with your favorite crackers or vegetables as dippers.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place peeled eggs in a jar.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over eggs.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 days.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Butter 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Drain chilies.
Remove seeds, pat dry and cut into 1-inch strips.
Mix together eggs, flour and half and half.
Pour in a little of this mixture into pan, then chilies, then cheese.
Continue to layer these items until gone, retaining 1 cup mixed cheese for topping.
Mix one can tomato sauce and salsa.
Pour over top, then top with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for approximately 50 minutes.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: jimmy carter peanut butter balls
directions: Blend margarine, peanut butter, Rice Krispies and powdered sugar with hands.
(May use a little more peanut butter if they don't stick together.)
Form into balls and freeze overnight. Melt bark in microwave in paper bowl.
Dip balls in bark and place on wax paper to cool.
Place on cookie sheets before freezing. When frozen, store in closed bag or bowl before serving.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter; press evenly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix milk and sugar and bring to a boil.
Lower flame and cook until it forms a ball in cold water.
Add margarine, vanilla and pecans and using a wooden spoon, beat until slightly creamy.
Stop when ripples show at the edges.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. If mixture hardens, set on low heat.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Generously grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Mix undiluted soup, milk and sherry in a large bowl until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, and toss gently to mix. Turn into prepared dish.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Bake 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker shell.
Freeze.
Can be served with strawberries, raspberries or a lime slice. Delicious for summer.

title: taffee
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Butter hands and pull taffee between two people.
Continue pulling until taffee is stretched.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Allow to cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt butter. Add pepper and pimientos.
Cook until warm.
Add green beans.
In another saucepan, combine soup, Carnation milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until center comes out clean when tested.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sift
together	flour, baking powder,
salt
and
sugar. Combine
beaten
eggs, milk and oil.
Stir	liquid	ingredients into
dry ingredients until barely blended.
Turn
batter
into greased and floured pizza or other large flat pan.	Spoon crumb topping over batter.
Sprinkle with blueberries or other cup of fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at	400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: hash
directions: Cook beef and pork until tender.
(Can be cooked in a crock-pot overnight.)
Chop meat and put back in pot with other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
You may put a bottle of barbecue sauce in recipe, if you would like.

title: cheese spread
directions: Blend together the cream cheese and butter.
Add all the spices and blend together well.
Chill.
Spread on crackers.

title: short ribs of beef
directions: Place the short ribs in a large saucepan with enough water to cover.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring water to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 3 hours, adding more water if needed.
During the last hour of simmering, add the onions. During last 30 minutes, add potatoes.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain 1 cup syrup off of fruit cocktail or pineapple; heat to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in it; add lemon juice and cool.
Stir in cottage cheese and whipped milk (or Cool Whip); fold in 1 1/2 cups fruit cocktail or pineapple and chill.

title: escalloped eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant in small amount of water.
Drain and mash until soft and fluffy.
Add salt to taste.
Saute onion in butter.
Add to eggplant with bread.
Add half the grated cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add 2 eggs and beat well.
Put mixture into buttered casserole. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugars, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix lemon jello, sugar and hot water.
Stir well.
Add apples, bananas, pineapple and pecans.
Mix and put in refrigerator until set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make this cake in layers.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix
all ingredients well.
Press through cookie press. Bake at 350° until lightly golden brown.
(Do not overcook.)

title: cherry bars
directions: First Layer:
Mix first 3 ingredients together in a 9 x 9 pan and press into bottom of pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° (325° for glass pans).

title: zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and shake well.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix flour and sugars together. Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until set. Double recipe exactly for 2 pies.

title: party meatballs
directions: Cook meatballs according to directions on package.
Heat sauce, jelly and wine until mixture is smooth.
Put meatballs in a chafing dish or crock-pot.
Pour sauce mixture over meatballs and heat on low about 30 minutes before serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Place layer of beans, cornbread, bacon, onion, pepper and tomatoes.
Mix mayonnaise with pickle juice.
Pour over salad. Let set for 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream; spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix ground beef and taco seasoning (cook as directed on taco seasoning package).
Cool and spread on cream mix. Sprinkle with garlic powder and 3 chopped green onions.
Add to the top of meat mixture, shredded sharp cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
When ready to serve, heat in oven for a few minutes and serve with corn chips.

title: sweet paska
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk which has been scalded, but cooled to lukewarm.
Add 3 cups flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix and let rise until double in bulk and bubbly (about 2 hours).

title: overnight sticky buns
directions: Place rolls in well-greased Bundt pan.
Pour on melted butter. Combine pudding and brown sugar; sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Cover pan tightly with towel.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Turn oven to 350° and bake rolls for about 30 minutes. Invert onto plate and serve.

title: best ever cinnamon rolls
directions: Cook 1 stick margarine, vanilla pudding and milk, adding 1 teaspoon salt; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat eggs; add to pudding mixture along with 2 cups flour.
Add yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on breadboard; add more flour.
Blend well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Turn out on board and roll out.
Cover with a mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and soft butter.
Roll, cut and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and let rise again.
Let rise again, bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: meat ball pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add meat balls and gravy, carrots, parsley and Worcestershire.
Heat until bubbling.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Mix cereal, sesame seed and salt.
Brush tops of biscuits in with milk; then dip in cereal mixture.
Arrange biscuits atop hot meat.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: fried shrimp dumplings
directions: Put
shrimp,
egg white, salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons of bread crumbs (or 1 slice of bread, cubed) in a food processor. Grind
about
seconds,
until the mixture is smooth. Shape like
oysters.
Roll
in bread crumbs and fry in hot oil at
350°. Drain
on
paper
towels.
Yield:
12 to 15 pieces.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts and fry in butter.
Place in roasting pan.
Sprinkle Good Seasons Italian dressing mix over chicken, saving 1 teaspoon to season rice.
Mix together mushroom soup, chicken soup, sour cream and white wine.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Cook rice according to directions.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger and cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage in large pieces.
Place in bottom of greased casserole.
Brown hamburg and onion.
Season to taste.
Pour off fat and stir in rice.
Place meat mixture on top of cabbage and cover evenly with tomato soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant fans(aubergines en eventail for 4)
directions: If only the large, egg-shaped eggplant is available, split it and cut it into slices crosswise.

Otherwise, split the small elongated variety; place the halves, split side down, on the chopped board and cut each, leaving the slices attached at the stem end, into 1/3-inch thicknesses, forming "fans".

Slip tomato slices into the slits of the sectioned eggplant halves and arrange them, gently forced together, side by side, in a large, oiled gratin dish, on the bottom of which has been scattered half of the chopped onion and sliced garlic.

title: p-nut butter chip cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine in oven.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with chips.
Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.* Cut into bars.
(Store loosely covered at room temperature.)

title: nancy's rice dish
directions: Make the Golden Saute, then set it aside.
Cook the sausage, then drain off the fat.
Add the celery and onions and cook until just tender.
Now stir all this into the golden saute and enjoy it with a salad.

title: morgan's mai tai
directions: Flash blend and float 1 ounce Myers rum!
Sit back and enjoy!

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easter sweet bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour in warm bowl.
Add flour gradually as needed and knead dough 10 minutes.
Cover and let rise to double size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into 2 or 3 loaves.
Brush with beaten egg and let rise again in cookie sheet.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Do not overcook.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice, onion and garlic in margarine in skillet until rice is golden brown.
Add water, bouillon, basil, cumin, tomato, salt and pepper; mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Top with cheese.
Let stand for several minutes to melt cheese.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and remove from bone. Cook celery, onion and 1/2 stick margarine in chicken broth. Add salt, pepper, sage and poultry seasoning to this and thicken with flour or cornstarch. Mix together 1 stick melted margarine and bag of stuffing.

title: fresh lemon tonic
directions: Stir lemon juice and sugar together until sugar is dissolved. Add whole cloves.
Serve over 1 or 2 ice cubes in each glass. Garnish with a lemon slice.

title: sandra's brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in pan.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with cocoa mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Beat 3 eggs, add 1/2 cup sugar, 1 stick melted margarine, yeast dissolved in 1 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Beat well.
Add 5 cups flour and mix.
Let rise overnight in well-greased bowl. Put dough on floured surface.
Divide in 3 equal parts.
Roll each part pie shaped.
Spread with melted margarine.
Cut into 8 or 16 equal parts.
Roll up, beginning at large end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make sure small end is on bottom.
Let rise 4 hours. Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: sassy onion dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Stir before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all except chips and cheese together in a bowl.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer ingredients as follows: chips, 1/2 of mixture and cheese.
Repeat.
Heat in oven until hot at 400°.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover.
Rinse beans, then place them in a 4-quart saucepot and cover again with water.
Cook over high heat until the water boils rapidly.
Drain beans into a colander.
Rinse with cold water.
Wash pot to remove all starch accumulated on sides.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Cream well. Add dry ingredients and then fold in cereals.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drop batter from teaspoon.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: betty's e-z salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Add sugar, bananas and strawberry pie filling.
Stir and chill.

title: five cheese spaghetti
directions: Mix cheeses together until well blended.
Butter large casserole dish (at least 2 quart).
Mix garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and mustard in bottom of dish.
Place 1/3 of spaghetti in casserole and top with 1/3 of cheeses.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Dot with margarine.
Repeat process 2 more times.
Pour milk over cheese and spaghetti.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Using 2 forks, lift spaghetti from the bottom several times to prevent a crust forming on top. Return to oven and bake another 15 minutes.
Repeat and bake 15 more minutes.
Serves 6.
This is excellent to microwave, reducing cooking time but still lifting during the process.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into meatballs.
Place in baking dish (do not brown).

title: one pot dinner beans
directions: Stir together.
Cover and cook until done, 4 to 6 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 2 bread pans lined with waxed paper or oiled.
Or use 2 (No. 2) size cans, well greased (to make round).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: north-south corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and shortening.
Mix well.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sour cream and sugar together.
Add 1/2 flour at a time with one egg yolk.
Continue this until all flour and egg yolks are used.
Add salt and vanilla flavoring.
Then beat with mixer for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Add egg whites last. Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add preserves.
Add dry ingredients with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add nuts and raisins that have been dredged with small amount of the flour called for in recipe.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° until done.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Beat together; batter will be thick.
Pour and spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix seasonings in oil.
Drizzle 1/4 to 1/3 of mixture over crackers, mixing and stirring well.
Let stand about 5 minutes between applications.
Repeat applications until all the seasonings are mixed in. Store in tightly covered container. Keeps well.

title: barker balls
directions: Melt butter (in a large saucepan) and chocolate on low heat. When melted, add egg; stir.
Stir in powder sugar, nuts and marshmallows.
Remove from heat.
Blend well.
Shape in balls. Roll in coconut.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Combine ingredients into a dough.
Form into balls and bake at 400° on ungreased cookie sheet until set but not brown. While still warm, roll in powdered sugar. Cool and roll again in powdered sugar.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and egg in bowl.
Pour over butter in pan. Spoon on sliced peaches.
Pour 1/2 cup peach juice on cobbler.
Sprinkle top with sugar and pecans, if wanted.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frito pie
directions: Heat chilli and water until hot.
Put layer of Fritos in pan. Pour
of
chilli over them, then cover with layer of cheese. Put
remaining
layer
of Fritos, remaining chilli and another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Cream the brown sugar and shortening.
Add egg and water.
Add sifted flour with soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in a large bar pan.

title: ella's surprise chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with lemon pepper, paprika and flour (can also use nutmeg).
Saute in margarine over low heat until nice and golden brown.
Remove from skillet and put in casserole dish.
Chop up small onion and bell pepper; saute in skillet with the leftover margarine from browning chicken.
Pour in water, continuing to saute.
Pour over chicken.
Cook, covered with foil, in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: buttermilk salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in blender at low speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into a pint jar, cover tightly and store in refrigerator a few hours before serving.

title: supreme pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse and drain.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Combine crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic.
Add milk and cream cheese and then beaten egg.
Cook briefly for 3 to 4 minutes, until well blended and thick.
Stir in thawed broccoli.
Set aside.
Take one package of crescent rolls and line pie dish, covering sides and bottom, making a crust. Spoon the filling into pie dish.
Top with Jack cheese.
Cover top with second package of crescent rolls and seal edges.
Cut 3 to 4 slits in top for steam.
Brush top with milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covering top with foil after 20 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate carrots; cube apple.
Drain pineapple; save juice. Mix juice with flour and sugar.
Cook until clear, then add mayonnaise.
Stir well and cool.
Add to fruit.

title: sausage stuffed acorn squash
directions: Halve squash lengthwise; discard seeds.
Place cut side down in deep skillet in 1/2 inch of water.
Steam 15 minutes.
Drain well. Place cut side up in baking dish.
Cook sausage in skillet over medium heat, breaking up pieces with spoon until brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in crumbs, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Spoon into squash cavities, pressing down lightly.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until filling is brown and squash is heated through.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in a bowl in order listed.
Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on top.
Crumble bacon on top.
Chill. You can substitute Ranch dressing for mayonnaise.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut tips from wings and cut joints to make 2 pieces. (Discard tips.) Marinate chicken wings in sauce made from combining the first 8 ingredients. Cover and refrigerate overnight. When ready to cook, drain off sauce and reserve. Put wings in baking pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Baste with reserved sauce several times. Serve warm.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Put into pineapple juice and set aside.

title: fried turkey seasons
directions: Put in Norpro flavor injector and put in the turkey with this.

title: swiss steak
directions: Add salt and pepper to the flour and pound into meat.
Brown in a skillet with fat.
Then add onion and green pepper.
Cover and simmer slowly until tender, about 1 1/2 hours in a casserole dish or skillet at 300 degrees.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage	come
to room temperature.
Mix together, then gradually add
Bisquick.
Roll
into
egg
size balls.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cukes and onions into large bowl. Cover with salt and water. Let set for 3 hours. Drain water off. While cukes are soaking, stir and mix other ingredients. Place cukes into jars and pour season mixture over them. Place lids on jars and store in refrigerator.

title: deviled clams
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand until stuffing absorbs liquid. Spoon mixture into clam shells or small baking dishes. Sprinkle with additional crushed stuffing and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute first three ingredients together until wilted.
Add drained broccoli.
Mix all ingredients in skillet.
Cook until cheese melts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together until thick.
Deep
fry
5 to 7 minutes or until brown.

title: quick quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and meat in a blender. Blend for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Sprinkle cheese and meat over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: delicious meat lasagna
directions: Boil about 6 lasagna noodles until noodles are tender.
Add ground beef, chopped onions, bell pepper, salt, pepper and seasoning salt in a cooking pan.
Over medium-high heat, brown beef and drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce (leaving 1/3 of sauce in jar) and sugar to drained beef.
Continue stirring spaghetti sauce through ground beef.
In 9 x 12-inch baking pan, spread remaining 1/3 spaghetti sauce in bottom of pan.
Spread 3 cooked lasagna noodles across bottom of pan.
Add half spaghetti meat sauce over top noodles.
Sprinkle half Mozzarella and half Cheddar cheese on top of meat sauce mixture.
Apply remaining lasagna noodles on top of cheese.
Add remaining spaghetti meat sauce and remaining cheeses.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, egg, sugar and honey.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking soda, salt and lemon extract. Chill dough.

title: spicy mixed nuts
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; add nuts and Worcestershire sauce; cook and stir over low heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Place nuts in large bowl.
Combine seasonings; sprinkle over nuts and toss to coat.
Cool; store in airtight container at room temperature.
Yields 3 cups.

title: real peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in a 2-quart saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook on high heat until mixture becomes thick (very tight bubbles).
Add peanuts and continue to cook until mixture begins to turn tan in color.
Peanuts may pop.
Stir slowly constantly.
Add margarine; stir until mixed.
Add soda and stir until mixture foams to top of pan.
Add vanilla; stir until mixed. Pour onto greased pizza pan.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.
Use wooden spoon for stirring.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine, marshmallows and oil until smooth.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and pack into buttered tube pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from broth and use the amount of broth it calls for on Rice-A-Roni, then add soup, celery, almonds, onion and mayonnaise.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and place in bottom of baking dish. Add chicken.
Combine next 4 ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese at least 10 minutes before done.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheesy artichoke heart appetizers
directions: Unroll dough; press into bottom and sides of 15 x 10 pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Combine all ingredients; spread over crust and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and cut into pieces.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli with salt and water.
Drain, set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, cheese and seasonings.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add broccoli and cook 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and almonds.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: lorraine's date cake
directions: Cook dates in boiling water and soda.
Beat sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla; add to date mixture.
Add flour, salt and nuts. Bake at 350° until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 of baked cake in the bottom of a punch bowl, then add 1/2 of pudding, then slice 1/2 of bananas and add 1/2 of the crushed pineapple, and then 1/2 of pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and repeat process.
Put cherries and/or nuts on top.

title: janie's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In mixing bowl, combine butter and sugar.
Add egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour.
Bake in muffin pans at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: thumbprints(cookies)
directions: Cut butter into small bits; add vanilla and almond extract and mix.
Add cornstarch, sugar and flour.
Mix with spoon until combined.
Make balls with 1 tablespoon of dough.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make a dent in each cookie with your thumb. Put a little jam into each dent.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool on racks.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Blanch cauliflower and broccoli; rinse in cold water and drain. Combine all vegetables in a large bowl; toss to mix well and refrigerate.

title: hobo's dinner
directions: Shape hamburger into one patty.
Place potatoes, carrots and hamburger patty in center of 12-inch piece of foil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup mix.
Fold sides up over food several times so juices do not leak through.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage or ground chuck and drain. Cut cheese into chunks. Put all ingredients in crock-pot and let cook. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mama sensat's fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until soft-ball stage.
Add rest of ingredients.
Blend; pour into buttered 9 x 13 dish.
Cut when cool.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, sour milk, and shortening.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Put in greased pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20-25 minutes.

title: peach pie filling
directions: Wash peaches; cut from seed, leaving peeling on.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add peaches.
Cook until thick enough to spread.
Pack in hot jars.
Process 10 minutes in water bath. Make fried pies and eat.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend milk and juice of lemons.
Fold in coconut, pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Turn into 2 graham cracker crusts (baked). Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon pie
directions: In a large saucepan mix the lemon juice, grated peel and water together.
Mix together cornstarch and sugar. Add to water and juice mixture. Beat eggs in a separate bowl.
Bring sugar mixture to a boil.
Add one spoonful of sugar mixture to eggs, then slowly add eggs to sugar mixture.
Cook until thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Add meringue being sure it touches all sides. Bake until meringue browns in a 400° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Let cool in oven overnight before serving.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook 5 minutes in iron skillet the sugar, margarine and egg yolks.
Add dates and pecans.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Then add Rice Krispies.
Make balls and roll in coconut.

title: spanish rice
directions: Put the grease in skillet.
Add enough rice to cover bottom of skillet.
Add pieces of sweet pepper and onion.
Add chili powder and garlic salt.
Cook a few minutes on low.
Add the tomato sauce; cook on low until sauce cooks down.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: tropical salad bar
directions: In a small saucepan, bring vinegar and lime juice to a boil. In a medium bowl, combine the sugar, salt, mustard, celery seed and paprika.
Add lime juice mixture and stir until sugar dissolves.
Whisk in oil and onion until dressing is well mixed and slightly thickened; transfer to a jar or serving dish.
Chill.

title: instant yeast rolls
directions: Mix cold water, scalded milk, yeast, oil, sugar and salt. Beat eggs and add to yeast mixture.
Add to flour.	Mix and shape. Only raise once, about 1 hour at room temperature.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
On top, put 2 tablespoons butter mixed with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey chili  macaroni
directions: Saute ground turkey, onion and green pepper until meat is no longer pink.
Add broth; add macaroni and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients and cook until done.

title: glazed cornish hens(serves 4)
directions: Combine jelly and cinnamon in small saucepan; heat, stirring until melted.
Set aside.
Place hen halves, skin side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.
Roast in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Brush with apple jelly and cinnamon mixture.
Roast 25 to 30 minutes longer or until browned and tender.

title: italian sausage supper
directions: Cook meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes or until noodles are tender, adding more water if necessary.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in bowl.
Top with a cherry in center.
Chill.
Serves 8 people.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken.
You may use all white meat or combine with chicken leg quarters.
Debone.
Chop chicken.
Chop pickles (homemade sweet is the best to use).
Chop eggs.
Add remaining ingredients to taste.
Mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain grease.
Return to oven and bake for 20 more minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate treats
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate bits in microwave oven 3 minutes on 50% power.
Stir after each minute.
Mix everything in a 9-inch square pan and chill in the refrigerator.
Cut into segments.
Enjoy:

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook hen until tender; remove meat from bones.
Chop up meat. Return to broth.
Add onion and butter beans; cook for 30 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook stew down until ingredients are done, stirring often.

title: joan's chow-chow
directions: Soak cabbage and tomatoes in salt overnight.
Press out salt water.
Mix vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Combine with cabbage mixture and cook until done.
Can in pint jars and seal.

title: fudge sickles
directions: Mix and freeze in small Dixie cups.

title: s'mores
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Break graham cracker in half.
Place chocolate chips in center of cracker.
Put on mini marshmallows in each corner. Top with other half of graham cracker.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.
Press sandwich lightly.
Cool for 2 to 3 minutes. Serves 1.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and flour.
Blend thoroughly. Turn onto pastry cloth, which has had 1/4 cup sifted flour worked into it.
Knead dough lightly 1 minute.
Divide dough in 2 balls. Roll balls paper thin in 16-inch circles.
Place circles on clean dry towels.
Cover with another towel and let dry at room temperature (until dough feels like chamois; it requires several hours to complete the drying).

title: texas yum yum cake
directions: Mix margarine, flour, and 3/4 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar, vanilla, and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Blend 1 1/2 cups milk with chocolate pudding mix; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Blend 1 1/2 cups milk with vanilla pudding mix; spread over chocolate pudding.
Spread remaining cup of Cool Whip over vanilla pudding and sprinkle with remaining chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Beat egg and add cheese, mayonnaise, soups and onion.
Mix ingredients together and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place cooked broccoli in a greased casserole dish.
Pour mixture over broccoli; top with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Casserole may be prepared and stored overnight in refrigerator before baking.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.
Garnish with remaining onions; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots round way and cook until barely tender; drain. Chop pepper and onion and set aside with carrots.

title: orange shortbread "carrots"
directions: Preheat oven to 325.
Grease 2 baking sheets or line with nonstick baking parchment.
In a mixing bowl beat together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add all the remaining ingredients and begin to mix well.
Using your hands, bring the mixture together to form a soft dough.
On a lightly floured surface, divide dough into 16 equal pieces.
Roll each piece of dough into a ball using the palms of your hands.
Roll backward and forwards so that one end begins to get thinner and you produce a carrot shape. Repeat with the remaining dough and lift onto baking sheets.
Using the back of a knife, lightly score marks all over the carrots.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle slices with salt and pepper. Mix cornmeal, Parmesan cheese and oregano in shallow dish. Heat oil in skillet. Coat tomato slices with cornmeal mixture. Place slices in skillet and fry 1 to 3 minutes on each side, until light brown. Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: salmon mold
directions: Place the salmon in a colander, pour boiling water over it and drain.
Remove the skin and bones; flake the fish.
Soak the gelatin in the cold water.
In a saucepan, mix the egg, mustard, salt, sugar, pepper and vinegar.
Add the skim milk and cool over very low heat, stirring constantly, until the custard coats the spoon.
Remove from heat, add the gelatin and stir until dissolved. Add the flaked salmon.
Pour into a 4-cup ring mold or fish mold that has been rinsed with water.
Chill until set.
Run the tip of small sharp knife around the inside of the mold.
Hold the bottom of the mold in hot water for a few seconds, and unmold onto a serving platter on which you have arranged a bed of sliced endive.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain excess fat. Add kidney beans, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Cook slowly 1 or 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned apple stack cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for apples, like biscuit dough.
Divide dough into 6 balls.
Roll out thin.
Bake each in a cake pan at 400° until brown.
When cool, put applesauce or cooked fresh apples between each layer.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer, combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix and pack the first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until done; drain.
Combine butter, sugar, lemon juice and paprika in skillet.
Heat over medium heat until bubbly.
Add carrots.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until glazed, stirring constantly.

title: kay's sausage and peppers
directions: Brown sausage after cutting into 1-inch pieces (link) or bite size pieces (bulk).
Transfer to pot.
Add peppers and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle good amount of garlic powder and oregano over meat mixture.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Serve on good rolls.

title: delicious bean pot
directions: Brown sausage in pan.
Pour off the excess fat.
Mix all ingredients and bake in crock-pot on high (325°), about 3 hours. Nothing in this recipe needs to be exact.
You can always add more beans or brown sugar, if you want more.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Cut out top core of each whole onion.
Place beef bouillon cube in onion and a
pat of butter.
Wrap individual onion in foil and bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in egg, milk and jalapenos.
Drop by teaspoons into hot, deep oil and fry until golden brown.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse with cool water. Drain canned fruit well. Cook sugar, salt, flour and eggs; cool. Then mix all together except marshmallows and Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight. May freeze this fruit mixture. Add Cool Whip to the amount of salad you want to use; add marshmallows. Makes a large salad.

title: weekend casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to instructions on package.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until transparent.
Add curry, soup, sour cream, wine, fish, Worcestershire and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fold sauce and noodles together and pour into a buttered casserole.
Top with cheese, oregano and paprika and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, soda, salt, milk, eggs, corn and bacon grease. Grease pan; cover with yellow cornmeal and brown.
Layer half of cornmeal mixture on the bottom of pan, then layer peppers, hamburger, onions and cheese.
Put remaining half of cornmeal mixture on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Heat water and bouillon cube to a boil.
Add broccoli and carrot.
Cook according to package directions and remove from heat.
Do not drain.
Finely chop onion and saute in small amount of oil; add to broccoli and carrots.
In separate saucepan make a white sauce by melting margarine and slowly stirring in flour. Continue stirring while gradually adding milk.
Stir in cheese, chicken soup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli mixture to white sauce mixture and cook over low heat until desired degree of thickness.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: very cheesy casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and herbs in butter, until onion is soft.
Combine all but last 3 ingredients.
Spread mixture in large, buttered oblong pan.
Top with sliced tomatoes. Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: spinach crescents
directions: Mix spinach, cheese and bacon in frypan and stir until cheese is melted.
Separate crescent rolls and cut each one into 2 pieces lengthwise.
Put a spoonful of spinach mixture on crescent roll and roll up, starting with large end.
Put on greased pan and bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For a quick dinner dish, just add diced, cooked meat before baking.

title: sauce for cabbage rolls
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake in a 350° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet. Brown the uncooked oatmeal in the melted shortening. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift together remaining ingredients and stir into creamed mixture. Chill dough (overnight if you want). Roll into balls the size of small walnuts. Roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon. Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake until lightly browned in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops. Yield: about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine
first five ingredients in blender;
beat until sugar dissolves.	Continue
to beat, slowly adding oil.
Stir in poppy seed.
Cover and chill.
Stir before serving.
Yield: 1 3/4 cups.

title: sally's chicken strata(serves 8 to 12)
directions: First Layer:
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with crustless bread.

title: horseradish relish
directions: Wash the horseradish well, then peel off all brown skin using a vegetable peeler.
Grate or chop enough of horseradish to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Mix with the rest of ingredients.
Pack into jars, store in refrigerator and let mellow for 2 weeks.

title: carrot sauce
directions: Drain cooked carrots.
Mix over low heat and set aside.
Put carrots back in pan after drained and pour sauce over carrots and toss.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Combine buttermilk and vinegar.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vinegar mixture and beat well.
Add food coloring and mix together.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra tightly into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Place a garlic clove and a hot pepper in each.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon into hot deep oil.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix the following ingredients together at least 5 minutes with electric mixer:
powdered sugar, eggs and butter.
Blend in 1 medium Cool Whip, then mix in fruit.
Put nuts on top just before serving.
Enjoy!!

title: yeast bread
directions: First 3 ingredients in bowl and set 10 minutes in a warm place, then add to the next mixture.
Second mixture is hot water in large bowl (cool slightly), shortening, salt and remaining sugar.
Warm flour over flame of oven top in a dish; move fast until warm.
Add yeast mixture and knead 500 times (about 7 to 10 minutes), then place in greased pan and let rise.
Then knead 100 times; rise again and knead down.
Place in buns and roll about third time.
Let buns rest in pan and bake until golden.

title: edith's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Put dates and soda in bowl and pour hot water over ingredients.
Cool.
Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Sift salt, flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Place beef in oblong baking dish.
Heat consomme, apple juice, soy sauce, garlic and onion powder to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour mixture on beef.
Cover and refrigerate, spooning mixture over beef occasionally, at least 3 hours.
Thread 4 or 5 cubes on each of 6 to 8 skewers.
Broil kabobs with tops, about 4-inches from heat, about 7 minutes or until done to taste.
Turn.
Also good cooked on your outdoor grill.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange evenly in greased 2-quart baking dish: potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and parsley (if desired).
Then mix ground beef, milk, catsup, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Spread this over potatoes.
Decorate top with more catsup, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour, until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix first ingredients and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle package of dry onion soup over top.
Lay pieces of frying chicken on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° (325° for glass dish).
Nice and easy.

title: blueberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until firm in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: citrus-cucumber salad
directions: Section grapefruit, catching juice.
Add sections of grapefruit, cucumbers, soy sauce and sesame seed.
Toss and serve on bowl lined with lettuce leaves.

title: puff bowl(mexican salad bowl)
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once.
Stir vigorously until well-blended.
Cook and stir mixture over medium heat until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, to mixture in pan, beating vigorously until smooth, about 1 minute after each addition.
Batter should look thick and feel slightly sticky.
Spread over bottom and up sides of a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden.
Cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Spread this mixture over drained pineapple.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Heat milk, butter and vanilla until butter melts.
Stir together sugar and cocoa.
Add to milk mixture when sugar has dissolved.
Let boil for 1 to 2 minutes, being careful not to let the mixture burn.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until well blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies to coat.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: chocolate chip date nut cake
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and soda.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and add date and water mixture.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour batter into pan.
Before baking, sprinkle top with chocolate chips, chopped nuts and powdered sugar.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: little indian pudding(recipe from pioneer days)
directions: Combine cornmeal and water.
Scald milk.
Add cornmeal mixture, stirring to prevent lumps.
Cook 20 minutes or until thickened.
Add salt, spices and molasses.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole or baking dish.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for at least 2 hours.
Serve warm with heavy cream, vanilla ice cream or hard sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork slowly in hot shortening.
Add 1 cup water, bouillon cube and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add reserved syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add sauce to pork.
Mix well.
Stir in pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes, or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tapioca(duchess cream)
directions: Beat egg until foamy.
Add sugar, gradually, and continue beating, until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in milk, salt and Minute tapioca. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 20 minutes.
Fold in marshmallows and pineapple.
Chill. Fold in Cool Whip and maraschino cherries. Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish, line with chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed. Pour this on top of casserole.
Dribble melted butter over dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and pour in pan (8-inch round or square glass pan).

title: waffled french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients in a shallow bowl.
Dip day old slices of bread in mixture one at a time and plate on hot waffle iron.
Cook until brown.
Works better if the crust is trimmed from bread. Serve hot with butter, syrup and powdered sugar.

title: potato and egg scramble
directions: Cook bacon slices in a frypan until crisp.
Remove from pan. Fry the potatoes in bacon fat until they are well browned, sprinkling with salt when they start to brown.
Cover pan closely and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Combine eggs, milk and pepper. Pour over potatoes in the pan and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set.
Crumble the bacon and add it just before taking the pan from the heat.
Serve at once. If desired, sliced, boiled potatoes may be used instead of raw potatoes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pecans.
Spread out in plate or roll up in a ball.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt butter or margarine and mix with flour and nuts (use your hands to do it!).
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Shake it all together.

title: beef verde
directions: Cut stew meat into small chunks.
Brown meat, then add onion and garlic to saute.
Add all other ingredients.
Let simmer on low heat 4 to 5 hours (can also be made in crock-pot).
Use a hand potato masher and mash cooked verde to shred meat and tomatoes. Serve when ready with flour tortillas and rice with sour cream. Also good to top potatoes with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been buttered.

title: nonfat blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar and fat free margarine together by hand.
Dough will be sticky.
Put half of dough in bottom of a glass square dish that has been lightly sprayed with Pam.
Put blueberries on top of dough.
Drop remainder of dough by spoonfuls on top of blueberries.
Mix the vanilla flavoring with the skim milk and then pour over the cobbler.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until top crust is brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and chill 2 hours.

title: alice's special gumbo
directions: Boil roast with onions and sausage until falls apart.
This is your secret stock.
Add gumbo seasoning pack and cayenne pepper to taste.
Serve over fluffy rice with green salad and crackers.

title: mexican corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: shellfish casserole
directions: Combine V-8 and mayonnaise.
Mix together crab, shrimp, rice, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Pour liquid over rice mixture; mix lightly.
Put in casserole. Top with bread crumbs and almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly hot.
Freezes well. Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated vegetables salad
directions: Drain vegetables, rinse in cold water.
Combine all ingredients, stirring gently, to mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: potatoes deluxe ii
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, margarine, cheese and salt in large bowl.
Add potatoes and onion.
Mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's rice custard
directions: Heat milk.
Add rice and margarine.
Add sugar, salt and raisins to beaten eggs, then slowly stir in the hot milk mixture. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased baking dish; set in a pan of hot water.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of custard.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine and mix first 3 ingredients.
Add at low speed flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, carrots, walnuts and vanilla.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix and cool lemon jello and boiling water.
Mix with beater until extremely smooth, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Whip with beater until stiff, whipping cream.
Keep refrigerated until ready to pour entire mixture into crust.
Pour jello mix into cream cheese mix.
Blend together, then blend in whipped cream. Pour mixture into prepared rusts.
Chill uncovered in refrigerator until firm (3 to 4 hours.).

title: blueberry delight
directions: Place berries in Pyrex dish. Cream the sugar and margarine. Add egg and flour.
Spread lightly and bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: chicken in a bag
directions: Mix all
except
chicken and cook on High for 2 minutes in microwave.	Dip chicken and place in brown paper bag.
Fold end and place
in second bag.
Place bags in platter for 18 to 21 minutes on High until done.

title: lime salad
directions: Stir mixture.
Put in dish.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: tupperware cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place on greased 9 x 13-inch pan, not touching.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Salt and pepper carrots.
In a container, layer carrots, onion and green pepper.
Prepare a sauce with the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients; spread on crust.
Top with assorted vegetables: onion, cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, olives, radishes, celery, etc.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes clean.

title: cream fruit dressing
directions: Beat eggs until light in double boiler.
Beat in sugar, butter, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over boiling water and stir until consistency of custard.
Cool and fold in 1 cup of whipped cream, which should be stiff.
Put on mixed fruit salad when ready to serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Soften butter to room temperature and mix in other ingredients.
Pinch off small pieces, roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Make a small dent in center and fill with a dot of jelly.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: ann mcculloch's chicken diable
directions: Wash chicken pieces; pat dry.
Remove skin if you wish.
Melt butter in shallow baking dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll chicken in this butter mix to coat.
Arrange meaty side up in single layer in same pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour until tender and lightly glazed.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Roll chicken parts in flour.
Brown onions and mushrooms.
Add tomato soup, sour cream, bay leaf, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add chicken. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: garlic roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl; toss to coat well.
Spread in jelly roll pan.
Roast 40 to 45 minutes until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add potatoes.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice per directions.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix together and add butter, 3/4 of the Cheez Whiz, can of soup and chicken (if desired).
Stir until cheese and butter are mostly melted.
Top with remaining Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Pour into a large casserole dish. Mix eggs and milk; add to spaghetti and mix.
Add spaghetti sauce. Brown meat and onion; drain and add to casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes before cutting into serving sections.

title: impossible pie
directions: Have eggs, butter or oleo and Bisquick at room temperature and beat together well.
Add vanilla, sugar, milk and coconut.
Bake in greased pie pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pie makes its own crust as it bakes.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, squash, oil and eggs; beat until well blended.
Stir in water.
Stir together flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to squash mixture and mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° (depending on oven) for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: o. j. punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl first three ingredients.
Add sherbet just before serving time.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil frying chicken; cool.
Bone and place chicken in bottom of casserole.
Pour soup and milk mixture over chicken.
Mix chicken broth and dressing mix.
Spoon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer until brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole(low-fat)
directions: Broil chicken breasts in salt, pepper and garlic powder until slightly brown.
Mix together mushroom soup, bouillon cube, uncooked rice and milk in bowl.
Pour rice mixture into casserole dish (have it large enough as rice will expand).
Top with chicken breasts and bake, covered, in 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Combine bulghar and boiling water in a bowl.
Cover and let stand until bulghar is soft, about 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Mix together.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Let set 5 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: black-eyed pea salad(yields 6 servings)
directions: Place black-eyed peas and water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 30 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold running water.
Place in a large bowl.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together except sherbet. One half hour before serving, set sherbet out of the freezer. Float sherbet in punch.

title: quick goulash
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Drain grease.
Cook macaroni and cheese.
Mix all together.

title: mud pie
directions: Grease a round 8 x 1 1/2-inch pan or 8 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate with shortening.
Mix sugar, butter, vanilla, salt, eggs, flour and cocoa in a medium bowl with a wooden spoon; stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together in a saucepan. Remove from stove.
Mix in powdered sugar. Stir until smooth.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Cut in squares and serve.

title: nique's italian sunset salad
directions: Halve cucumber lengthwise; scrape out seeds with a spoon. Slice cucumbers into half moons.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Spoon onto 4 serving plates.
Drizzle vinaigrette on top.

title: microwave meat loaf ring
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients except catsup.
Pack lightly into a 9-inch glass cake dish or quiche dish, making a well in the center and placing a custard cup upside-down in center of the dish.

title: granola
directions: Mix all together, except chocolate chips, and put in oven for 1 hour at 300°.
When done, add chocolate chips and stir.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Beat
the egg.	Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and baking
powder
that have been sifted together.
Chop the peeled, raw
apples and add them with the nuts to the batter. Turn	into a well-greased 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for
30 minutes.
Serve
warm or cold with whipped cream, ice cream or hard sauce.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Put all ingredients in a bowl; knead to mix well (this takes some time). Shape into 1-inch balls; place on baking sheet.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown.
Serve hot.
This recipe will serve a large group.
Sausage balls are a tradition in our family on Christmas Eve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 80 small balls.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Chill pickles and onion in salted water for 3 hours.
Heat spices, vinegar and sugar.
Add pickles and onions.
Bring to boil.
Put in jars.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together starting with the Cool Whip and sour cream.
Mix together well, then add the rest of the ingredients.

title: scalloped carrots and cheese
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain. In a saucepan, gently cook onion in margarine 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in flour, salt and mustard, then milk, cooking and stirring until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange a layer of carrots, then cheese.
Repeat, ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil and cool.
Dissolve Jell-O in 9 cups of boiling water and cool.
Add juice to sugar and Jell-O mixture and freeze.

title: 15 minute cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter, mixing well.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wet bread slices with hot water; squeeze out excess water. Mix bread, sausage and spices together.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Top with tomato sauce or catsup and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: award winning pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pumpkin filling evenly in bottom of pie crust.

title: chocolate coconut dips
directions: Mix water, syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Boil to soft ball stage and add the coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. When coconut is cool, over hot water, melt chocolate.
Dip the coconut into the chocolate.
Allow to cool well on wax paper.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook zucchini in boiling water until tender.
Drain, then mash in a large bowl.
Add the cheese, egg, crackers, and butter.
Mix well.
Add nutmeg.
