Transfer to an ovenproof dish and bake until mixture thickens, approximately 1/2 hour.
Test with a bread knife, if it comes out fairly dry, the dish is done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish.
Combine stuffing mix with melted butter or oleo and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl. Microwave 1 minute. Stir in milk, sour cream, onion, garlic powder, pepper, green peppers and beef. Mix well. Melt butter. Stir in pecans and Texas Pete. Mix well and serve on crackers as dip.

title: punch
directions: Add water to make one gallon.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat electric skillet to 280°.
Combine sugar, margarine and milk in skillet.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn together.
Pour into a greased casserole (about 2-quart size).
Mix salt, onion, sour cream, celery soup and cheese together.
Spread over beans and corn mixture.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine, then spread on top of casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Layer half of potatoes in bottom of large casserole.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Top with remaining sliced potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Add butter while potatoes are hot. Add other ingredients.
Mash with masher until soft.
Put into pie crusts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: aunt ruby's canned green beans
directions: Cover with water.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: pineapple and cheese casserole
directions: Mix flour and pineapple juice together.
Drain pineapple; save juice.
Melt butter.
Pour into mixture.
Add sugar, pineapple and cheese.
Mix well together.
Pour into baking dish; crumble crackers on top of mixture and pour a small amount of butter on top of crackers.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until middle is done. Thinner it is, the less time it will take.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly with hand beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour filling in pie shell.
Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Refrigerate any remaining pie immediately.

title: chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts in greased loaf pan. Top each piece with cheese. Arrange mushrooms. Mix soup and wine. Pour over all chicken. Spread stuffing mix. Drizzle melted margarine over all. Bake
1 hour or until done.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs and sour cream.
Put soda and cream of tartar in flour and sift enough to make stiff batter.
Add vanilla.
Drop with teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Shape 20 meatballs.
Brown well in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Drain excess fat.
Sprinkle meatballs with 1 tablespoon flour; stir gently to coat.
Combine 1 (28 ounce) can tomatoes, cut into bite size pieces, 1/2 cup Heinz 57 sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until desired consistency.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; add bread crumbs (or cracker).
Shape into oval loaf 2 to 2 1/2-inches thick.
Cover all sides with flour.
In heavy skillet, brown on both sides, turning once. Drain; add water to cover half of loaf.
Heat, then cover and simmer 1 hour.
Move around occasionally to prevent burning. Add potato and carrot chunks.
Dot with butter; add more water, if desired.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Remove all to platter. Add milk, using flour and water to thicken gravy.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Cream eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Pour into can. Add condensed milk and stir well.
Add milk to fill line on can. Makes 4 quarts.

title: frozen tropical salad
directions: Mix together and freeze several hours.
Serve partially frozen.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface.
Cut with flower cookie cutter.
Bake on greased baking sheet for about 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add next four ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour in a prepared loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: simple banana nut bread
directions: Blend together the sugar and shortening.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: wilcox's real hash browns(made easy, but like the restaurant)
directions: Shred potatoes into colander.
Rinse thoroughly under running cold water to remove all starch.
Fry until done.
Excellent taste and texture, and fast!

title: lemon delight
directions: Chill cream; then beat in lemon juice and sugar.
Crumble in vanilla wafers and chill until ready to serve.

title: crusty scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°C.
Combine crumbs and melted margarine. Save 125 ml crumb-margarine mixture for topping.
Press crumbs evenly on sides and bottom of pie pan.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and sugar.
Slowly add milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Mix in corn and eggs.
Stir well.
Pour corn mixture into crumb crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until a knife inserted (off center) comes out clean.

title: heavenly coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 (8-inch) round layers according to directions. Split cooled layers horizontally.
(Use piece of thread between forefinger and thumb.)
Combine sour cream, coconut and sugar in a mixing bowl, stirring well.
Spread 1 1/4 cups of mixture between cake layers.
Combine remaining sour cream mix with whipped topping.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Chill; slice to serve.

title: ruby slipper cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until creamy. Spoon 1/3 of batter into well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with gelatin.
Spoon another 1/3 of batter over gelatin.
Sprinkle remaining gelatin over batter.
Spread remaining batter over gelatin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan with 2/3 crumb mixture. Fill with softened ice cream (or any kind you prefer). Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top. Cover with foil and freeze.
Serve with hot fudge syrup. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; sprinkle with salt, and cover with cold water; let stand 2 hours; drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, and spices in large pot; bring to a boil.
Add vegetables, return to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of the margarine and blend in flour.
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Prepare au jus mix as directed with 2 cups water.
Add au jus gradually to flour, stirring with a whisk until thickened and smooth.
Simmer 1 minute.
Add catsup, bouillon cubes dissolved in hot water, pepper, paprika and garlic powder. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Keep warm.
Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll in medium balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: polvorones
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Add lard to dry ingredients and blend well.
Add eggs and knead by hand in bowl until ingredients are blended and dough is smooth.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll into small balls about the size of a nickel.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 350° (until golden brown).
Remove sheets from oven onto wire racks and cool slightly.
Using a spatula, remove two or three cookies at a time from cookie sheet.
Gently place on platter on which you have put the cinnamon and sugar.
(One cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, mixed.)
Coat generously and with slotted spoon, remove to serving platter.
Makes six to seven dozen.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Put cooking oil in skillet.
Sprinkle flour on top of oil; stir as it browns.
When brown, pour in tomatoes and water.
Stir constantly until gravy is thick.
Delicious with homemade biscuits.

title: pastel punch
directions: Mix everything and serve in 4 ounce cups.

title: nut rolls
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Add enough flour to make firm dough.
Chill overnight.
Break off pieces of dough the size of a walnut.
Roll very thin in granulated sugar.
Spread with nut filling and roll as for jelly roll.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven pan stew
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and season.
Do not add any water as it will make its own juice.
Cook in a moderately hot oven (about 325°) for 3 hours or until the meat is done.
Stir once in awhile to keep from sticking.

title: meatballs in tangy sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, tomato sauce, lemon juice, garlic salt and wine; bring to a boil, stirring. Reduce heat and allow to simmer gently, uncovered, until sauce is thickened (about 20 minutes).

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Chop onion and celery fine and combine with oil, vinegar, mustard, ketchup and seasonings.
Pour mixture over shrimp.
Let set overnight, turning once or twice to cover shrimp.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix like you would biscuits.
Put in refrigerator to get cold. Cut like you would biscuits.
Bake at 450°.
These are delicious with ham.

title: breakfast burrito tacito
directions: Crumble up sausage patties; cook and drain meat.
Pull out of pan; cook hash browns and eggs in some of sausage grease.
Put sausage and picante sauce back into egg/hash brown mixture. Remove from heat; warm flour tortillas.
Put 1/4 mixture into each flour tortilla.
Roll up; serve warm.

title: tammy's stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, onion, green pepper, garlic and spices in a skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes.
Simmer for a couple of hours.
Cook shells.

title: blender sweetened condensed milk
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.

title: sweet pickle
directions: Pack large cucumbers in a
gallon
jar;
add salt, alum and spice.
Fill jar with vinegar.
Put lid on and let set for 6 weeks.
Drain.
Slice cucumbers
thin.
Place
a
layer
of sugar and a layer of cucumbers.
Let set several hours.
Makes its own syrup.
It's okay to seal or not seal.

title: beef burgundy(all cooking is done in the oven)
directions: Mix all together, except the wine.
Put in casserole that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours; at the end of 2 hours, add the wine.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Slice and lightly brown hot dogs in frypan.
Add tomato sauce, green chilies, water, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add noodles. Slice cheese and lay over entire hot dog-noodle mixture.
Tear tortillas into pieces and place on top, covering well.
Place lid on top and cook on low for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon and egg and beat well.
Add both milks and beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruity treats
directions: Melt margarine in microwave; mix in marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are well coated.
Cover and microwave about 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred.
Pour Fruity Pebbles, all at once, into marshmallows.
Stir until well mixed.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press firmly with wax paper.
Cool and cut.

title: springtime salad
directions: Combine vegetables, bacon and cheese.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise together and add to vegetables.
Stir; add salt and pepper, if desired.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch strips. Cover with water and cook until crisp-tender. Drain and set aside. Combine 1/4 cup butter, sour cream, soup, onion, salt, pepper and mushrooms in large bowl. Mix well. Add potatoes and cheese. Stir gently. Pour into a greased oblong Pyrex dish. Mix 3 tablespoons butter and stuffing. Sprinkle on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: breakaway vegetable bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters; dip each into melted margarine and layer 1/3 in a lightly-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with half of the bacon, cheese, onion and green pepper.
Repeat layer until all ingredients are used, ending with biscuits.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch pan and dot with butter on top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soups, broth, Ro-Tel and cheese. Pour over chicken in long casserole dish. Crumble crackers; mix with melted margarine. Spread over chicken and soup mixture. Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and cornstarch to boil and keep stirring until thick.
Add Jell-O mix and stir well.
Remove from heat; mix in cut up berries.
Pour in pie shell and refrigerate.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, 1/2 can tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into loaf and place in a greased loaf pan.
With wire whip combine 1/2 can tomato sauce, water, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar.
Add prepared sauce on top and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste loaf several times while baking.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Melt margarine and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to box instructions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix sugar and cream cheese together and drop by teaspoon on top of cake.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: 12 step soft pretzels(philadelphia style)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/8 cup warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups warm water and the brown sugar. Add the flour gradually and continue stirring (add 1 cup at a time). Beat until smooth. Knead dough on a floured surface until smooth.
Heat oven to 475°.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice together.
Layer in pan 1/2 each of soup mix, then chicken, then broccoli and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: southern baked pecans
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add pecans and salt.
Stir well. Remove from heat and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until tender. Peel and shred.

Combine shredded potatoes with sour cream, onions, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper. Turn mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dessert for a crowd
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Crush crackers into fine crumbs.
Place egg whites in large bowl with baking powder and beat until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts, mixing well.
Spread into greased baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inches) and bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
In a bowl, cream softened cream cheese until light.
Fold in whipped topping and well drained fruit.
Spread over cooled crust; cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with coconut and cut into squares; serve.

title: corn stew
directions: Salt and brown beef.
Drain; add onion and pepper.
Over medium heat add tomatoes.
Use a fork and stir tomatoes into small chunks.
When onions and peppers are cooked, add tomato soup and corn.
When stew is hot, add Cheez Whiz.
Stir until all ingredients are well mixed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put crackers over top and pour butter over all.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers, about 1/2 thick slices.
Mix slices with salt and let set overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into favorite pie crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and baking soda.
Allow to stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cream in sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add vanilla, nuts and flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into mixture.
Divide into 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans.
When cool, spread on cake.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Beat together cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Add chocolate chips.
Fill cupcake papers half full with cake mix that was mixed as directed on cake mix box.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Combine pudding, cinnamon and brown sugar in small bowl.
Cut rolls in pieces (4 to 6) when partially thawed (15 minutes).
Put a little of 1st mixture into bottom of pan, then layer rolls and pudding mixture.
(Use tube or Bundt pan.)
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine.
Let rise all night.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jiffy breakfast(microwave recipe)
directions: Lightly grease or spray a 6 ounce custard cup.
Press meat in the bottom to form a cup.
Break an egg on top of the meat. Pierce the yolk gently once with fork.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover the cup with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 1 to 3 minutes.
Place egg and meat on top of toast.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, Crisco, salt, butter and peanut butter until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and vanilla.
Stir.
Shape into balls 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Slice bananas and add over layer of cookies.
Repeat until bowl is full.
Mix milk, cup of sugar, flour, salt, egg yolks, vanilla and butter together for pudding.
Cook like custard and pour over bananas and cookies.
Mix egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar. Pour over pudding.
Brown and serve.
Hint:
Make in oven-safe dish.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cream all ingredients.
Store in covered container, no need to refrigerate.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl combine sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Blend well.
Shape dough into balls.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls in mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn and peanuts in large roasting pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes; do not stir.
Remove from heat. Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour gradually over popcorn and peanuts, mixing well.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine and sift flour, spices, soda and salt.
Cream margarine.
Add brown sugar gradually and cream well.
Add Scramblers, 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Add the dry ingredients alternately with applesauce, blending well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: creamy swiss chocolate bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. This forms the base. Combine the rest of the ingredients for the topping.
Mix well and pour on top of base. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: smoked sausage and cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up sausage.
Pare and slice potatoes.
Place potatoes in large skillet.
Slice onion and place in layer over potatoes.
Add layer of thinly sliced cabbage.
Add butter and salt to boiling water, stirring to melt.
Pour over vegetables.
Place pieces of sausage on top and sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly and cook on low for 22 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli to package directions. Drain well.
Mix broccoli, soup and egg.
Turn into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle crumbs on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clam sauce
directions: In a large skillet, fry onion and clams in olive oil until onion is tender.
Add garlic powder, red pepper and salt.
Add tomatoes along with the juice and simmer for about 1 hour.
The longer it simmers, the better it tastes.

title: pecan delight
directions: Melt butter; combine flour, butter and pecans.
Press into bottom of cake pan to form crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: jenny's french dip sandwiches(servings:  8)
directions: Place roast in Dutch oven.
Slice onion in thin slices and put on top.
Put onion soup mix in and then pour consomme and sherry over all.
Bake (uncovered) at 325° for 2 hours.
Remove roast from pan and thinly slice.
Put slices back into the pan and cook in oven an additional 45 minutes.
Slice rolls and butter them. Broil until toasted.
Place cheese slices on bottom, then put meat slices and onion on top.
Serve with a cup of sauce for dipping.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Place drained beans into casserole dish with a cover.
Saute onions in butter.
Add sour cream; season with salt and pepper. Stir thoroughly and pour over beans.
Cover and bake in 350° preheated oven for 1/2 hour.

title: christmas jello
directions: Make in layers.
For layer one, mix cherry jello according to directions on package.
Add sliced banana and pour into mold that has been greased with mayonnaise.
Allow this layer to set.
For second layer, mix lemon jello with proper amount of water and add mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Pour this mixture over first layer and allow to set.
Mix lime jello, using pineapple juice as part of water measurement.
Add pineapple and pour over second layer.

title: cheesy hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain well.
Add taco seasoning and chili.
In a separate pan, dice up the Velveeta, cook on low heat stirring constantly.
Add hamburger mixture.
Serve with chips.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 12 x 9 x 3-inch greased pan.

title: mama's rolls
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Set in a warm place covered with a light dish cloth.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out on a lightly floured board 3/4-inch thick.
(You can also roll them into balls and place three balls to a muffin tin for cloverleaf rolls.)
Cut rolls out with biscuit cutter and place on well-greased pan and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in 425° oven until brown.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, and powdered sugar until smooth. Pour into baked pie shell. Spread pie filling on top.
May add crushed Oreo cookies on top. Chill until ready to eat.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and oil until soft.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and powder together.
Add milk and flavoring to butter, then add walnuts last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: aunt serena's chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in dishpan.
Cook on medium-low heat, stirring often, until thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: fruit balls (bullets)
directions: Chop nuts and dates; mix with coconut, sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well and add eggs, well beaten. Make into balls the size of walnuts and roll in coarse sugar.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Will be sticky.

title: smorgasbord cheesecake
directions: Mix together crumbs, margarine and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Press into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese and 3 tablespoons sour cream; blend until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.

title: creole dip
directions: Saute meat, onions, pepper and celery in oleo.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add pimento and juice, then add all other ingredients.
Serve warm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain and set aside. Cook ground beef and onions in a large skillet until meat is browned. Drain well. Stir in macaroni, chili beans and next 4 ingredients. Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25
minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes. Sprinkle corn chips on top.

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls.
Press with fork, if dough seems dry, add a little water.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: german spice cake
directions: Make a liquid from 1/2 cup coffee and 1 cup water.
Cream margarine and add sugar and whole egg and nutmeats.
Put spices in flour.
Make up coffee and strain.
Mix coffee with enough flour to make a liquid paste.
Put baking powder in balance of flour mixture.
Mix alternately flour and coffee with creamed mixture. Bake in any pan, round, square or tube style, well-greased.
Put in unlighted oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with chocolate frosting.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Dissolve sugar, syrup and salt in the hot water. Cook, without stirring, to firm-ball stage. Remove from heat and pour gradually over stiffly beaten egg whites. Add vanilla, beating constantly, until mixture has lost its gloss. Spoon out on wax paper sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Press out with hand, then spread peanut butter. Roll up and wrap in wax paper and foil. Refrigerate.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in glass casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Stir while cooking.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls and press onto large cookie sheet. Sprinkle crescent rolls with 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons of Hidden Valley party dip.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream, cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and remaining Hidden Valley party dip. Spread mixture on top of dough.
Top in order with broccoli, carrots, mushrooms, bacon and cheese.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: ritzy crackers
directions: Combine milk and dates.
Cook slowly until mixture thickens to spreading consistency, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chopped nuts.
Spread on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool completely!

title: fresh dilly cucumbers and onions
directions: Measure 2 tablespoons salt into a small container.
Peel and slice the onions into a glass pie plate.
Sprinkle with some of the salt.
Peel and slice the cucumbers over the onions, sprinkling salt on each layer.
Let stand 10 minutes, then drain very well.
Mix together the vinegar, salad oil and sugar; add to the cucumber-onion mixture.
Toss to coat well.
Place in an airtight container (I use a jar).
Place a sprig of fresh dill in bottom, center and top of mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, mash yams with margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, except pastry shell and eggs.
Beat until mixture is smooth and well blended.
Stir in eggs.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomatoes and crusts, together. Toss lightly.
Then mix in tomatoes lightly.
Place in pie tin. Cover and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 425°.
Serve warm as apple pie.

title: dried beef chicken breasts
directions: Shred dried beef over bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole dish (approximately).
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Mix soup, sherry and sour cream and pour over chicken and dried beef.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until chicken is done on oven temperature of 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Roll chicken in flour, then brown in butter.
Remove chicken. Stir soup, seasonings and water or broth into drippings.
Cook and stir to a boil.
